Kind: captions
Language: en-US

00:02:31.533 --> 00:02:34.570
IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE 19th CENTURY

00:02:34.570 --> 00:02:37.606
TWO BROTHERS,
ORSON AND LORENZO FOWLER

00:02:37.606 --> 00:02:40.209
MADE AND SOLD BUSTS
LIKE THIS ONE.

00:02:40.209 --> 00:02:44.113
SUPPOSEDLY BY READING
THIS MAP OF THE HEAD AND FACE

00:02:44.113 --> 00:02:46.281
YOU COULD EVALUATE
SOMEONE'S CHARACTER

00:02:46.281 --> 00:02:47.583
AND PERSONALITY

00:02:47.583 --> 00:02:49.318
EVEN PREDICT HIS BEHAVIOR.

00:02:49.318 --> 00:02:51.053
HERE IS WHERE YOU WOULD LOOK

00:02:51.053 --> 00:02:53.222
TO SEE IF HE HAD
SELFISH SENTIMENTS.

00:02:53.222 --> 00:02:55.391
OVER HERE IS
DOMESTIC PROPENSITIES.

00:02:55.391 --> 00:02:57.993
THIS ONE, OF COURSE,
IS FOR INTUITIVE REASONING

00:02:57.993 --> 00:03:00.162
AND REFLECTIVE FACULTIES

00:03:00.162 --> 00:03:02.765
MORAL AND RELIGIOUS SENTIMENTS

00:03:02.765 --> 00:03:04.500
SELF-ESTEEM, POWER OF WILL.

00:03:04.500 --> 00:03:06.669
THE SYSTEM IS CALLED PHRENOLOGY

00:03:06.669 --> 00:03:09.271
AND IT WAS ONE OF
THE MORE POPULAR THEORIES

00:03:09.271 --> 00:03:11.440
ABOUT HUMAN BEHAVIOR
AT THE TIME.

00:03:11.440 --> 00:03:14.476
TOO BAD IT WASN'T BASED
ON SCIENTIFIC EVIDENCE.

00:03:14.910 --> 00:03:17.946
ACTUALLY, IT'S ONLY TOWARDS
THE END OF THE 19th CENTURY

00:03:17.946 --> 00:03:20.983
THAT SCIENTISTS TURN THEIR GAZE
ON HUMAN BEHAVIOR--

00:03:20.983 --> 00:03:25.320
TRADITIONALLY THE PROVINCE
OF PHILOSOPHERS, POETS

00:03:25.320 --> 00:03:29.658
THESE SCIENTISTS TRIED TO MAKE
THE SEEMINGLY IRRATIONAL
RATIONAL.

00:03:29.658 --> 00:03:31.827
THEY TRIED TO SORT OUT
WHAT IN HUMAN BEHAVIOR

00:03:32.261 --> 00:03:33.562
IS FIXED AT BIRTH

00:03:33.562 --> 00:03:36.165
AND WHAT IS LEARNED
THROUGH EXPERIENCE.

00:03:36.165 --> 00:03:40.069
IT IS A JOURNEY THAT TWISTS
AND TURNS THROUGHOUT THE CENTURY

00:03:40.069 --> 00:03:42.671
AS THEY AND WE GO
"IN SEARCH OF OURSELVES."

00:03:47.443 --> 00:03:50.045
AT THE TURN OF THE CENTURY

00:03:50.045 --> 00:03:53.082
DOCTE
MYSTERIES OF THE HUMAN MIND

00:03:53.082 --> 00:03:59.154
ARE DRAWN TO THIS VENERABLE
HOSPITAL IN PARIS: SALPETRIERE.

00:04:01.323 --> 00:04:03.926
BUILT AS AN ARSENAL
IN THE 16th CENTURY

00:04:03.926 --> 00:04:10.432
SALPETRIERE IS ANYTHING
BUT AN ORDINARY HOSPITAL.

00:04:10.432 --> 00:04:12.167
BY THE LATE 19th CENTURY

00:04:12.167 --> 00:04:14.770
IT HAS BEEN TRANSFORMED
INTO THE LEADING CENTER

00:04:14.770 --> 00:04:17.806
FOR THE STUDY OF A STRANGE
AND PERPLEXING MALADY--

00:04:18.240 --> 00:04:19.975
HYSTERIA.

00:04:21.276 --> 00:04:23.790
A MALADY WHICH BECOMES
THE PASSION

00:04:23.790 --> 00:04:27.349
OF ITS IRON-WILLED DIRECTOR,
JEAN MARTIN CHARCOT.

00:04:28.650 --> 00:04:31.253
CHARCOT, BY ALL ACCOUNTS
OF CONTEMPORARIES

00:04:31.253 --> 00:04:36.458
WAS A COLDAUTHORITARIAN FIG
URE

00:04:36.458 --> 00:04:38.193
AND THIS IS WHAT CAUSED HIM

00:04:38.193 --> 00:04:41.230
TO BE CALLED THE NAPOLEON
OF THE NEUROSES.

00:04:42.965 --> 00:04:46.001
Woman:
IN THE SALPETRIERE

00:04:46.001 --> 00:04:48.974
THERE WAS A HUGE POPULATION
OF PATIENTS WHO SUFFER

00:04:50.339 --> 00:04:52.941
ONE OF THE MURKIEST DISORDERS
STILL AROUND.

00:04:52.941 --> 00:04:54.243
THAT WAS HYSTERIA.

00:04:54.676 --> 00:04:55.978
AND IT WAS A NEW OPPORTUNITY.

00:04:55.978 --> 00:04:57.713
IT WAS AN OPPORTUNITY
FOR CHARCOT

00:04:57.713 --> 00:05:00.315
TO BRING ALL THE SKILLS
HE HAD AS A NEUROLOGIST

00:05:00.315 --> 00:05:02.050
TO FINALLY UNPACK THE SECRETS

00:05:02.050 --> 00:05:04.219
OF ONE OF THE MOST
FRUSTRATING DISORDERS

00:05:04.219 --> 00:05:05.521
FOR CLINICIANS OF THE TIME.

00:05:08.557 --> 00:05:12.027
Osgood:
CHARCOT OBSERVES PATIENTS
WITH A DIZZYING ARRAY

00:05:12.027 --> 00:05:14.630
OF-

00:05:14.630 --> 00:05:16.799
SPASMS...

00:05:16.799 --> 00:05:18.967
PARALYSIS...

00:05:18.967 --> 00:05:22.437
BLINDNESS...

00:05:22.437 --> 00:05:25.908
AMNESIA...

00:05:25.908 --> 00:05:31.547
EVERY PHYSICAL AND BEHAVIORAL
ABNORMALITY IMAGINABLE

00:05:31.547 --> 00:05:35.017
ALL WITHOUT A TRACEABLE CAUSE.

00:05:38.053 --> 00:05:40.656
AT THE HEIGHT OF HIS CAREER

00:05:40.656 --> 00:05:44.560
CHARCOT TURNS HIS FULL ATTENTION
TO HYSTERIA

00:05:44.560 --> 00:05:46.728
CERTAIN HE CAN FIND ITS CAUSE.

00:05:48.030 --> 00:05:50.199
HE IS NOT THE FIRST TO TRY.

00:05:51.934 --> 00:05:54.102
Woman:
THE GREEKS BELIEVED

00:05:54.102 --> 00:05:56.271
SED
Woman:
THEBY THE UTERUSVEDWAS CAU

00:05:56.271 --> 00:05:58.874
BY THE UTERUS

00:05:58.874 --> 00:06:00.609
AS AN UNATTACHED ORGAN

00:06:00.609 --> 00:06:03.212
KIND OF LIKE A BEACH BALL
INSIDE THE BODY

00:06:03.212 --> 00:06:04.947
AND SHIFTING AROUND.

00:06:04.947 --> 00:06:07.549
SO THAT MONDAY
IT MIGHT BE IN YOUR NECK

00:06:07.549 --> 00:06:09.718
AND TUESDAY
IT MIGHT BE IN YOUR WRIST

00:06:09.718 --> 00:06:11.887
AND WEDNESDAY
IT MIGHT BE IN YOUR STOMACH.

00:06:11.887 --> 00:06:14.056
AND WHEREVER THIS UTERUS
HAPPENED TO END UP

00:06:14.056 --> 00:06:15.791
IT CREATED SYMPTOMS--

00:06:15.791 --> 00:06:17.960
"THE WANDERING WOMB,"
AS THEY USED TO CALL IT.

00:06:24.466 --> 00:06:27.502
HYSTERIA IS STILL TIED
TO FEMALE SEXUALITY.

00:06:31.406 --> 00:06:34.443
MAKES HER ESPECIALLY VULNERABLE
IS WIDELY HELD.

00:06:37.045 --> 00:06:40.082
"AFTER ALL," REMARKS ONE
OF CHARCOT?? COLLEAGUES

00:06:40.082 --> 00:06:42.251
"HOW COULD MEN HAVE HYSTERIA?

00:06:42.251 --> 00:06:44.419
THEY HAVE NO UTERUS."

00:06:45.721 --> 00:06:47.890
Micale:
MANY DOCTORS OF THE TIME,
IN FACT

00:06:47.890 --> 00:06:51.360
BELIEVED THAT HYSTERIA WASN'T
A REAL DISEASE AT ALL.

00:06:51.360 --> 00:06:53.528
HYSTERIA THEY DISMISSED

00:06:53.528 --> 00:06:58.300
AS ARTIFICIAL
OR SIMULATING BEHAVIOR

00:06:58.300 --> 00:07:01.336
OR PERHAPS, WHENT APPEARED
IN FEMALE PATIENTS

00:07:01.336 --> 00:07:03.939
AS A FORM OF SEXUAL PROMISCUITY

00:07:03.939 --> 00:07:07.843
THAT WAS THEREFORE CONTEMPTIBLE
ON MORAL GROUNDS.

00:07:07.843 --> 00:07:11.313
CHARCOT, HOWEVER, ARGUED

00:07:11.313 --> 00:07:13.916
THROUGHOUT THE COURSE
OF HIS CAREER

00:07:13.916 --> 00:07:16.084
THAT HYSTERIA, IN FACT

00:07:16.084 --> 00:07:19.121
WAS A SUBJECT
OF LEGITIMATE SCIENTIFIC STUDY.

00:07:21.723 --> 00:07:24.760
Osgood:
HYSTERIA CANNOT BE
A WOMAN'S DISEASE

00:07:25.193 --> 00:07:27.362
BECAUSE MEN SUFFER, TOO.

00:07:27.362 --> 00:07:29.097
CHARCOT BELIEVES INSTEAD

00:07:29.097 --> 00:07:33.001
THAT A BRAIN DISEASE
CAUSES HYSTERIA

00:07:33.001 --> 00:07:37.773
AND THAT ONLY CERTAIN PEOPLE
SUCCUMB TO IT--

00:07:37.773 --> 00:07:39.942
THOSE FROM TAINTED STOCK.

00:07:46.882 --> 00:07:50.352
IT IS PASSED DOWN
FROM GENERATION TO GENERATION.

00:07:52.955 --> 00:07:56.858
YET CHARCOT IS NOT BOTHERED
WHEN HE CANNOT FIND HYSTERIA

00:07:56.858 --> 00:07:59.895
IN THE EXTENDED FAMILIES
OF HIS PATIENTS.

00:08:02.382 --> 00:08:05.968
Micale:
CHARCOT COULD ARGUE
THAT HYSTERIA COULD TRANSMUTE

00:08:05.968 --> 00:08:11.086
INTO OTHER TOTALLY DIFFERENT
PATHOLOGICAL FORMS

00:08:11.086 --> 00:08:14.209
SUCH AS EPILEPSY
OR PARKINSON'S DISEASE

00:08:14.209 --> 00:08:16.378
OR MULTIPLE SCLEROSIS.

00:08:16.378 --> 00:08:19.414
WITH THE HINDSIGHT
OF A HUNDRED YEARS, OF COURSE

00:08:19.414 --> 00:08:21.149
THIS SEEMS
ABSOLUTELY RIDICULOUS.

00:08:21.149 --> 00:08:24.186
THESE ARE TOTALLY SEPARATE
PATHOLOGICAL CATEGORIES

00:08:24.186 --> 00:08:26.788
WITH DIFFERENT CAUSES
AND DIFFERENT COURSES

00:08:26.788 --> 00:08:28.523
AND DIFFERENT THERAPEUTICS.

00:08:28.523 --> 00:08:29.825
A HUNDRED YEARS AGO, HOWEVER

00:08:30.258 --> 00:08:32.861
THEY WERE VERY INDISCRIMINATELY
LUMPED TOGETHER.

00:08:32.861 --> 00:08:35.030
CHARCOT WAS GOING TO TAKE

00:08:35.030 --> 00:08:38.500
THIS VAST AMORPHOUS WASTEBASKET
CATEGORY OF SYMPTOMS

00:08:38.500 --> 00:08:40.669
THAT WAS CALLED HYSTERIA

00:08:40.669 --> 00:08:43.705
ATION
OF EVERY CLINICIAN USTR

00:08:43.705 --> 00:08:46.742
IN EVERY MAJOR HOSPITAL
FOR CENTURIES, EFFECTIVELY

00:08:46.742 --> 00:08:49.344
AND HE WAS GOING TO REPLACE IT

00:08:49.344 --> 00:08:52.814
WITH AN ELEGANT
NEUROPHYSIOLOGICALLY BASED MODEL

00:08:52.814 --> 00:08:54.549
OF ITS ETIOLOGY AND COURSE.

00:08:54.549 --> 00:08:57.586
HE WAS BASICALLY GOING
TO MAKE HYSTERIA LIE DOWN

00:08:57.586 --> 00:08:59.694
AND REVEAL ITS LAWS.

00:09:02.357 --> 00:09:05.394
Osgood:
NOW, C
OF HYSTERIA'S CAUSE

00:09:05.394 --> 00:09:08.430
CHARCOT TURNS TO CATEGORIZING
ITS SYMPTOMS.

00:09:13.635 --> 00:09:16.671
HE SKETCHES EVERY MOVEMENT
OF HIS PATIENTS

00:09:16.671 --> 00:09:19.274
IN VIVID DETAIL.

00:09:31.420 --> 00:09:34.890
WHEN THE NEW ART OF
SCIENTIFIC PHOTOGRAPHY APPEARS

00:09:34.890 --> 00:09:37.492
CHARCOT FINDS
AN EVEN BETTER METHOD

00:09:37.492 --> 00:09:39.661
TO CAPTURE THE NUANCES
OF BEHAVIOR.

00:09:42.697 --> 00:09:44.433
HE HIRES A PHOTOGRAPHER

00:09:44.433 --> 00:09:47.035
TO WORK FULL TIE
AT SALPETRIERE.

00:09:50.505 --> 00:09:52.240
CHARCOT WAS AVISUEL.

00:09:52.240 --> 00:09:54.409
HE LOVED TO SEE THINGS
WITH HIS EYE

00:09:54.409 --> 00:09:55.710
AND SEE THEM IN SUCH A WAY

00:09:55.710 --> 00:09:57.879
THAT HE COULD
THEN STUDY THEM EXACTLY.

00:09:58.313 --> 00:10:00.482
AND PHOTOGRAPHY ENABLED YOU
TO STOP TIME.

00:10:00.482 --> 00:10:02.651
THAT IS, IT ENABLED YOU
TO TAKE A SYMPTOM

00:10:02.651 --> 00:10:07.856
STOP IT, ISOLATE IT AND THEN
TO LOOK AT IT IN DETAIL.

00:10:07.856 --> 00:10:10.892
Osgood:
CHARCOT DECLARES,
"THE CAMERA DOES NOT LIE."

00:10:14.362 --> 00:10:17.399
IT WOULD BECOME AS CRUCIAL
TO HIS STUDY OF HYSTERIA

00:10:17.833 --> 00:10:20.869
AS THE MICROSCOPE IS
FOR BIOLOGISTS.

00:10:23.905 --> 00:10:27.375
AUGUSTINE WAS ONE
OF CHARCOT'S FAVORITE PATIENTS.

00:10:27.375 --> 00:10:29.544
SHE WAS HIS SUPERMODEL.

00:10:29.544 --> 00:10:32.147
AUGUSTINE WAS YOUNG,
SHE WAS PRETTY

00:10:32.147 --> 00:10:34.316
SHE WAS VERY WELL DEVELOPED.

00:10:34.316 --> 00:10:36.918
HE POINTS ALL OF THIS OUT
IN HIS BOOKS.

00:10:37.352 --> 00:10:39.087
AND SHE RESPONDED WELL
TO THE CAMERA.

00:10:51.233 --> 00:10:54.703
Osgood:
CHARCOT WILL TAKE SOME 10,000
PHOTOGRAPHS OF HIS PATIENTS...

00:11:02.944 --> 00:11:06.848
SEARCHING FOR A PATTERN
IN THE PANOPLY OF SYMPTOMS.

00:11:11.620 --> 00:11:15.090
CURIOUSLY, THESE SYMPTOMS
SEEM TO REFLECT

00:11:15.090 --> 00:11:17.692
THE CULTURE OF THE TIME.

00:11:17.692 --> 00:11:22.464
HE WAS PRODUCING PHOTOGRAPHS
OF BEAUTIFUL, SOMETIMES, WOMEN

00:11:22.464 --> 00:11:25.934
IN VERY ODD, BUT ALSO IN SOME
WAYS VERY FAMILIAR POSITIONS.

00:11:25.934 --> 00:11:27.669
IF YOU STUDY THE PHOTOGRAPHS

00:11:27.669 --> 00:11:29.838
OF THE HYSTERICS
IN THE SALPETRIERE

00:11:29.838 --> 00:11:31.573
YOU WILL SEE
THEY RESEMBLE VERY MUCH

00:11:31.573 --> 00:11:34.176
THE WOMEN IN PAINTINGS
OF THE RENAISSANCE.

00:11:34.176 --> 00:11:35.911
THIS IS NOT AN ACCIDENT.

00:11:35.911 --> 00:11:40.248
CHARCOT WAS A GREAT ADMIRER
OF PAINTING.

00:11:40.248 --> 00:11:41.983
HE SAW HIMSELF AS A MAN

00:11:41.983 --> 00:11:45.020
WHO WAS CULTIVATED,
ARTISTIC, LEARNED

00:11:45.020 --> 00:11:46.755
AND HE WANTED HIS OWN WORK

00:11:46.755 --> 00:11:49.357
TO INTERSECT
WITH FRENCH CULTURE GENERALLY

00:11:49.357 --> 00:11:51.092
AND IT DID.

00:11:51.092 --> 00:11:55.864
Osgood:
INTELLECTUALS AND THE PUBLIC
ALIKE TAKE GREAT INTEREST

00:11:55.864 --> 00:11:58.466
IN CHARCOT'S
SCIENTIFIC ENDEAVOR.

00:11:58.466 --> 00:12:00.635
HE BECOMES A CELEBRITY HIMSELF

00:12:00.635 --> 00:12:02.804
ON THE STREETS OF PARIS
AND BEYOND.

00:12:04.430 --> 00:12:06.708
RENOWNED FOR
HIS THEATRICAL FLAIR

00:12:06.708 --> 00:12:09.744
HE ATTRACTS A WIDE AUDIENCE
EVERY TUESDAY

00:12:09.744 --> 00:12:12.347
WHEN HE OFFERS
A LECTURE DEMONSTRATION

00:12:12.347 --> 00:12:14.950
FOR DOCTORS WHO COME
FROM AROUND THE WORLD

00:12:15.383 --> 00:12:17.986
TO SEE THE PROCLAIMED
"PRINCE OF SCIENCE."

00:12:22.757 --> 00:12:25.794
SOMETIMES PATIENTS
HE HAD NEVER SEEN BEFORE

00:12:25.794 --> 00:12:27.529
AND HE WOULD DIAGNOSE THEM.

00:12:27.529 --> 00:12:31.433
AND SOMETIMES PATIENTS CAME IN
HEHADTREATED BEFORE

00:12:31.433 --> 00:12:33.168
AND THEY WOULD BE HYPNOTIZED

00:12:33.602 --> 00:12:37.505
AND CHARCOT WOULD INSTRUCT THEM
TO HAVE HYSTERICAL SEIZURES.

00:12:37.939 --> 00:12:40.976
AND HE WOULD EXPLAIN WHAT WAS
GOING ON TO THE AUDIENCE.

00:12:40.976 --> 00:12:43.144
SO IT BECAME THE HOTTEST TICKET
IN PARIS.

00:12:43.144 --> 00:12:45.313
EVERYBODY WENT.

00:12:45.313 --> 00:12:49.217
EVERYBODY WHO WAS
IN THE MEDICAL WORLD HAD TO GO.

00:12:49.217 --> 00:12:53.555
BUT NOVELISTS WENT,
JOURNALISTS WENT, PAINTERS WENT.

00:12:53.555 --> 00:12:58.326
EVERYONE WHO WAS ANYONE
IN LATE-19th-CENTURY PARIS

00:12:58.326 --> 00:13:00.061
HAD TO GO.

00:13:01.796 --> 00:13:05.700
Osgood:
ONE MEMBER OF THE AUDIENCE
CAPTIVATED BY CHARCOT

00:13:05.700 --> 00:13:07.790
IS A YOUNG DOCTOR FROM VIENNA

00:13:07.790 --> 00:13:11.773
WHO IS JUST EMBARKING
ON HIS OWN CLINICAL CAREER--

00:13:11.773 --> 00:13:13.942
SIGMUND FREUD.

00:13:16.544 --> 00:13:18.713
FREUD HAS BEEN TRAINED
IN NEUROLOGY

00:13:18.713 --> 00:13:20.882
ATORIES
FREUD HAS BEEN TRAINED
IN NEUROLOGYPEAN LABOR

00:13:20.882 --> 00:13:26.955
STUDYING THE BRAINS OF EELS,
FISH AND EVENTUALLY HUMANS.

00:13:28.256 --> 00:13:32.594
BUT IN TIME, FREUD TURNS
AWAY FROM HIS MICROSCOPE.

00:13:32.910 --> 00:13:34.763
Man:
HE DID ALL
THE TRADITIONAL THINGS

00:13:34.763 --> 00:13:38.233
THAT PEOPLE WHO ARE GOING
TO GO INTO BIOLOGICAL SCIENCE

00:13:38.233 --> 00:13:39.534
WOULD DO AT THAT TIME

00:13:39.534 --> 00:13:43.004
AND HE WAS TRYING TO APPLY
THE THINKING THAT HE WAS DOING

00:13:43.004 --> 00:13:45.607
TO ISSUES OF
BEHAVIORAL ABNORMALITIES--

00:13:45.607 --> 00:13:46.908
DISTURBANCES THAT HE SAW

00:13:47.342 --> 00:13:49.511
IN PEOPLE THAT
HE WAS WORKING WITH--

00:13:49.511 --> 00:13:50.812
AND HE WAS VERY FRUSTRATED

00:13:50.812 --> 00:13:53.415
THAT ALTHOUGH
HE COULD STUDY THE BRAIN

00:13:53.415 --> 00:13:56.885
AND TRY TO LOOK AT ITS ANATOMY,
HE JUST NY WAY

00:13:56.885 --> 00:13:59.487
THAT THAT WORK COULD
BE DIRECTLY APPLICABLE

00:13:59.487 --> 00:14:02.957
TO THE CLINICAL PROBLEMS
THAT HE WAS CONCERNED WITH.

00:14:02.957 --> 00:14:05.994
Osgood:
WHILE STUDYING WITH CHARCOT
IN PARIS

00:14:05.994 --> 00:14:09.898
FREUD BECOMES FASCINATED
BY THE PATIENTS AT SALPETRIERE.

00:14:09.898 --> 00:14:12.934
BUT THE BRAIN-LESION THEORY
OF HIS FRENCH MENTOR

00:14:12.934 --> 00:14:15.537
DOES NOT MAKE SENSE.

00:14:17.706 --> 00:14:22.043
PATIENTS WITH PARALYZED HANDS
CAN STILL MOVE THEIR ARMS.

00:14:22.043 --> 00:14:27.682
THOSE WITH PARALYZED FEET
CAN STILL MOVE THEIR LEGS--

00:14:27.682 --> 00:14:30.719
MOVEMENTS THAT WOULD BE
COMPLETELY IMPOSSIBLE

00:14:30.719 --> 00:14:37.659
IF THEIR PARALYSIS WERE TRULY
CAUSED BY A BRAIN DISORDER.

00:14:37.659 --> 00:14:41.454
Harrington:
THE SYMPTOMS OF HYSTERIA
DIDN'T FOLLOW BIOLOGICAL LOGIC.

00:14:43.732 --> 00:14:46.334
IT FOLLOWED A KIND
OF A LAYMAN'S SENSE

00:14:46.334 --> 00:14:48.937
OF HOW PARALYSIS
PROBABLY SHOULD HAPPEN.

00:14:50.672 --> 00:14:52.407
Osgood:
FREUD'S DOUBTS INCREASE

00:14:52.407 --> 00:14:55.443
WHEN AUTOPSY AFTER AUTOPSY
OF HYSTERICAL PATIENTS

00:14:55.443 --> 00:14:57.612
YIELD NOTHING.

00:14:59.781 --> 00:15:03.251
THE HOPED-FOR BRAIN LESION
NEVER MATERIALIZES.

00:15:07.155 --> 00:15:09.758
BUT PERHAPS WHAT IS
MOST TROUBLING TO FREUD

00:15:09.758 --> 00:15:12.794
IS SOMETHING
MUCH CLOSER TO HOME.

00:15:12.794 --> 00:15:14.529
MANY EUROPEANS--

00:15:14.529 --> 00:15:17.565
FROM THE MAN ON THE STREET
TO THE MEDICAL ELITE--

00:15:17.565 --> 00:15:21.035
SHARE CHARCOT'S BELIEF
THAT CERTAIN TYPES OF PEOPLE

00:15:21.035 --> 00:15:24.939
ARE MORE PRONE TO DEGENERATE
INTO MADNESS...

00:15:26.674 --> 00:15:30.578
PEOPLE WHO COME
FROM WEAKENED STOCK

00:15:30.578 --> 00:15:32.747
BAD BLOOD.

00:15:36.651 --> 00:15:39.254
JEWS, AS A GROUP,
ARE SINGLED OUT.

00:15:39.254 --> 00:15:41.423
AND THE JEWISH COMMUNITY
IN VIENNA

00:15:41.423 --> 00:15:44.893
OF WHICH FREUD IS A MEMBER,
IS NO EXCEPTION.

00:15:45.326 --> 00:15:48.363
Micale:
ACCORDING TO
DEGENERATIONIST THEORY

00:15:48.363 --> 00:15:53.134
JEWS WERE MORE PRONE TO NERVOUS
AND NEUROTIC BREAKDOWN.

00:15:53.134 --> 00:15:57.472
THEY WERE INCLUDED
IN A CATEGORY OF CHARACTER TYPES

00:15:57.472 --> 00:15:59.641
THAT WERE PARTICULARLY
SUSCEPTIBLE

00:15:59.641 --> 00:16:01.376
TO NERVOUS DEGENERATION.

00:16:01.376 --> 00:16:05.713
UNDERSTANDABLY, FREUD IS
NOT SYMPATHETIC TO THIS IDEA.

00:16:05.713 --> 00:16:09.184
HE SENSES AN ANTI-SEMITIC
CONTENT IN IT

00:16:09.184 --> 00:16:11.352
AND I'M ALMOST CERTAIN

00:16:11.352 --> 00:16:20.462
THAT THIS IS A PERSONAL FACTOR
THAT ALLOWS HIM

00:16:20.462 --> 00:16:22.630
Osgood:
WITH THIS, FREUD CONCLUDES

00:16:22.630 --> 00:16:26.534
HIS COLLEAGUES HAVE FAILED
TO EXPLAIN MENTAL DISORDERS.

00:16:26.534 --> 00:16:29.571
THEY HAVE FOCUSED
ONLY ON THE PHYSICAL BODY

00:16:29.571 --> 00:16:32.607
IGNORING THE COMPLEXITY
OF THE MIND.

00:16:35.210 --> 00:16:38.246
FINDING HYSTERIA'S TRUE CAUSE,
HE BELIEVES

00:16:38.246 --> 00:16:40.415
REQUIRES A RADICALLY
NEW APPROACH

00:16:40.415 --> 00:16:44.319
WHICH FREUD WILL UNDERTAKE IN
HIS PRIVATE PRACTICE IN VIENNA.

00:16:44.319 --> 00:16:49.090
IN THE PROCESS, HE WILL SEEK
NOT ONLY TO EXPLAIN HYSTERIA

00:16:49.090 --> 00:16:50.825
BUT ALSO PRESENT

00:16:50.825 --> 00:16:54.729
THIS CENTURY'S FIRST
DISTINCTLY PSYCHOLOGICAL THEORY

00:16:54.729 --> 00:16:56.898
OF HUMAN BEHAVIOR.

00:16:56.898 --> 00:17:01.236
HIS FIRST CLUE COMES FROM
FELLOW NEUROLOGIST JOSEF BREUER

00:17:01.236 --> 00:17:03.838
AND BREUER'S PATIENT,
BERTHA PAPPENHEIM

00:17:03.838 --> 00:17:07.182
REFERRED TO AS "ANNA O."

00:17:07.182 --> 00:17:10.345
Micale:
PAPPENHEIM IS
A VERY YOUNG WOMAN;

00:17:10.345 --> 00:17:14.682
HAD SEARCHED OUT JOSEF BREUER
AND PRESENTED TO BREUER

00:17:14.682 --> 00:17:19.020
AN EXTRAORDINARY IDIOSYNCRATIC
SERIES OF SYMPTOMS.

00:17:19.020 --> 00:17:20.755
SHE WAS HAVING
DIFFICULTY SLEEPING.

00:17:20.755 --> 00:17:23.791
SHE WAS SUFFERING
FROM NIGHTMARES.

00:17:23.791 --> 00:17:27.262
IT WAS IMPOSSIBLE
FOR HER TO DRINK WATER

00:17:27.262 --> 00:17:31.165
AND IN THE MORE SEVERE STAGES
OF HER DISORDER

00:17:31.165 --> 00:17:35.937
SHE HAD LOST THE ABILITY
TO SPEAK HER NATIVE GERMAN.

00:17:41.576 --> 00:17:45.046
AND LATER TELLS

00:17:45.046 --> 00:17:46.781
TO A YOUNG SIGMUND FREUD.

00:17:49.817 --> 00:17:52.854
Osgood:
THROUGH HYPNOSIS,
BREUER COAXED ANNA O.

00:17:52.854 --> 00:17:56.758
TO REMEMBER WHEN
HER SYMPTOMS FIRST APPEARED...

00:17:57.191 --> 00:18:00.228
TO A TIME WHEN HER FATHER
BECAME GRAVELY ILL.

00:18:00.228 --> 00:18:03.264
ONCE SHE REMEMBERED
THIS TRAUMATIC EPISODE

00:18:03.264 --> 00:18:07.168
AND TALKED OPENLY ABOUT IT,
HER SYMPTOMS VANISHED.

00:18:07.168 --> 00:18:12.373
THIS BECOMES KNOWN AS
THE "TALKING CURE."

00:18:12.373 --> 00:18:15.410
FREUD NEVER ACTUALLY
MEETS ANNA O.

00:18:15.410 --> 00:18:17.579
BUT WHAT IMPRESSES HIM MOST

00:18:18.012 --> 00:18:20.615
IS THE PARTICULARITY
OF HER SYMPTOMS

00:18:21.006 --> 00:18:24.085
AND THEIR LINK
TO A PERSONAL TRAUMA.

00:18:24.085 --> 00:18:27.989
Harrington:
TO FREUD, THE SYMPTOMS
OF HYSTERIA REVEAL

00:18:27.989 --> 00:18:31.459
NOT WHAT'S WRONG
WITH A PATIENT'S BRAIN

00:18:31.459 --> 00:18:34.929
BUT, IN A SENSE, WHAT HAD GONE
WRONG IN THE PATIENT'S LIFE.

00:18:34.929 --> 00:18:38.833
THEY BECOME SYMPTOMS
OF TRAUMATIC EVENTS

00:18:38.833 --> 00:18:44.038
EMOTIONALLY INTOLERABLE EVENTS
THAT A PATIENT HAD REPRESSED

00:18:44.038 --> 00:18:48.376
AND THEREFORE, THAT RATHER
THAN FINDING EXPRESSION

00:18:48.376 --> 00:18:52.280
IN APPROPRIATEEMOTIONAL
AFF... UH, EXPRESSION

00:18:52.280 --> 00:18:54.882
FOUND EXPRESSION
IN BODILY SYMPTOMS.

00:18:57.051 --> 00:18:59.654
Osgood:
AFTER SEEING PATIENT
AFTER PATIENT

00:18:59.654 --> 00:19:02.606
FREUD BELIEVES THAT SYMPTOMS
ARE INVARIABLY BORN

00:19:02.606 --> 00:19:06.160
OUT OF PSYCHOLOGICAL TRAUMA.

00:19:06.160 --> 00:19:09.631
THEEANINGFUL
IN AND OF THEMSELVES

00:19:09.631 --> 00:19:11.799
BUT ACT AS A ROAD MAP

00:19:11.799 --> 00:19:15.703
TO A SUBMERGED INNER LIFE
THAT IS TROUBLED.

00:19:16.137 --> 00:19:20.041
Roth:
FREUD SAYS THAT HYSTERICS SUFFER
MAINLY FROM REMINISCENCES;

00:19:20.041 --> 00:19:22.210
THAT IS, WHAT CAUSES A SYMPTOM

00:19:22.210 --> 00:19:24.812
IS SOMETHING
IN THE PAST OF THE PATIENT

00:19:24.812 --> 00:19:29.584
THAT HE OR SHE CANNOT GET OVER,
CANNOT FACE, CANNOT THINK ABOUT

00:19:29.584 --> 00:19:32.620
AND THAT IT TAKES
AN ENORMOUS AMOUNT OF ENERGY

00:19:32.620 --> 00:19:35.657
TO STAY AWAY FROM
THAT PART OF THEIR PAST.

00:19:38.259 --> 00:19:41.729
Osgood:
SO TOXIC IS THIS MEMORY,
IT IS BANISHED

00:19:41.729 --> 00:19:49.103
TO A PART OF THE MIND WHICH
FREUD CALLS "THE UNCONSCIOUS."

00:19:49.103 --> 00:19:54.742
WHERE DREAMS AND SLIPS
OF THE TONGUE TAKE SHAPE...

00:19:54.742 --> 00:19:57.345
THE HOME OF FANTASIES
AND FEARS...

00:19:57.345 --> 00:20:01.249
OF UNCENSORED THOUGHTS
AND SEXUAL DESIRES...

00:20:04.719 --> 00:20:10.358
THE BIRTHPLACE, FREUD BELIEVES,
OF ALL EMOTIONAL TRAUMA.

00:20:12.527 --> 00:20:15.129
FROM HIS IDEA OF THE UNCONSCIOUS

00:20:15.129 --> 00:20:19.467
FREUD DEVELOPS PSYCHOANALYSIS,
A NEW THEORY OF THE MIND

00:20:19.467 --> 00:20:23.805
AND A TECHNIQUE
TO GAIN ACCESS TO IT--

00:20:23.805 --> 00:20:27.275
A THEORY THAT MANY
T.

00:20:29.877 --> 00:20:31.612
Micale:
FREUD IS ATTACKED
IN HIS OWN TIME

00:20:31.612 --> 00:20:33.781
ON A GREAT MANY
DIFFERENT GROUNDS.

00:20:33.781 --> 00:20:35.516
CERTAINLY THE MOST IMMEDIATE

00:20:35.516 --> 00:20:37.685
AND THE BEST KNOWN
OF THE GROUNDS

00:20:37.685 --> 00:20:41.155
WAS THAT HIS IDEAS
WERE PORNOGRAPHIC.

00:20:41.155 --> 00:20:45.059
BECAUSE HE DISCUSSES SEXUALITY
SO EXTENSIVELY

00:20:45.059 --> 00:20:48.963
AND IN SUCH A COLD,
NEUTRAL, ANALYTIC TONE

00:20:48.963 --> 00:20:53.301
THEY SEE THIS
AS MORALLY IMPERMISSIBLE.

00:20:56.771 --> 00:21:01.542
Osgood:
FREUD IS ALSO ATTACKED
FOR OTHER REASONS.

00:21:01.542 --> 00:21:08.049
THE UNCONSCIOUS CANNOT
BE SEEN OR TESTED.

00:21:08.049 --> 00:21:14.989
YOU CANNOT STUDY IT UNDER
A MICROSCOPE, OR DISSECT FOR IT.

00:21:14.989 --> 00:21:21.929
THERE IS NO MATERIAL PROOF
OF ITS EXISTENCE.

00:21:21.929 --> 00:21:24.532
TO SOME, FREUD'S
PSYCHOANALYSIS SEEMS

00:21:24.532 --> 00:21:32.340
TOO THEORETICAL, TOO
PHILOSOPHICAL, TOO UNSCIENTIFIC.

00:21:32.340 --> 00:21:36.244
Roth:
HE WAS NOT A SUCCESSFUL
THEORETICIAN IN THE EARLY YEARS.

00:21:36.244 --> 00:21:38.846
HIS WORK DID, HOWEVER, ATTRACT

00:21:38.846 --> 00:21:42.316
THE INTEREST OF
A FAITHFUL BAND OF ADHERENTS

00:21:42.316 --> 00:21:46.220
AND FREUD USED THEIR COMMITMENT
TO HIM AND TO PSYCHOANALYSIS

00:21:46.220 --> 00:21:49.690
AS THE BASIS FOR DEVELOPING
A PSYCHOANALYTIC MOVEMENT

00:21:50.124 --> 00:21:53.161
THAT RESEMBLES UNFORTUNATELY,
IN MY VIEW, IN MANY WAYS

00:21:53.161 --> 00:21:54.896
A CHURCH IN ITS EARLY YEARS--

00:21:54.896 --> 00:21:57.498
PEOPLE WHO HAVE TO BE COMMITTED

00:21:57.498 --> 00:22:00.968
TO THE CARDINAL CONCEPTS
OF PSYCHOANALYSIS

00:22:00.968 --> 00:22:04.438
IN ORDER TO BE TREATED
AS FAITHFUL ADHERENTS.

00:22:04.438 --> 00:22:08.342
Harrington:
FREUD WAS ABLE TO CREATE

00:22:08.342 --> 00:22:13.114
A KIND OF RELIGIOUS ZEAL
IN INTELLECTUALS

00:22:13.114 --> 00:22:15.716
MANY OF WHOM WERE JEWISH

00:22:15.716 --> 00:22:20.054
OR FELT, IN THE CONTEXT
OF VIENNESE SOCIETY

00:22:20.054 --> 00:22:22.223
SOMEWHAT MARGINALIZED.

00:22:22.223 --> 00:22:25.693
HERE THEY COULD BE AT THE CENTER
OF SOMETHING VERY EXCITING

00:22:25.693 --> 00:22:27.862
THAT WAS POTENTIALLY
GOING TO TRANSFORM

00:22:27.862 --> 00:22:30.031
THE WAY IN WHICH
WE THINK THE MIND WORKS.

00:22:31.766 --> 00:22:36.537
Osgood:
BY 1914, FREUD'S FOLLOWING
IS STILL RELATIVELY SMALL

00:22:36.537 --> 00:22:40.007
BUT THAT WILL ALL CHANGE SOON.

00:22:40.007 --> 00:22:43.911
POLITICAL EVENTS WILL THRUST
FREUD'S PSYCHOLOGICAL THEORIES

00:22:43.911 --> 00:22:45.646
ONTO A WORLD STAGE

00:22:45.646 --> 00:22:49.116
PROVIDING A BRUTAL
LIVING LABORATORY

00:22:49.116 --> 00:22:51.719
FOR THE EFFICACY
OF FREUD'S IDEAS.

00:22:55.189 --> 00:22:57.792
WORLD WAR I.

00:22:57.792 --> 00:23:01.696
GERMANY IS PITTED AGAINST
MOST OF EUROPE, RUSSIA

00:23:01.696 --> 00:23:05.600
AND LATER, THE UNITED STATES.

00:23:07.768 --> 00:23:10.805
Roth:
THE FIRST WORLD WAR WAS

00:23:10.805 --> 00:23:19.480
EUROPE'S ENCOUNTER WITH MASS
DESTRUCTION THROUGH TECHNOLOGY.

00:23:19.480 --> 00:23:22.950
YOU DIDN'T KILL SOMEONE
CLOSE UP.

00:23:22.950 --> 00:23:26.420
YOU WERE OFTEN
JUST LYING IN A DITCH

00:23:26.420 --> 00:23:32.493
AND SUDDENLY
SOMEONE NEXT TO YOU WOULD DIE

00:23:32.493 --> 00:23:36.831
BECAUSE AN EXPLOSION WOULD SEND
SHRAPNEL AND KILL THAT PERSON.

00:23:39.867 --> 00:23:44.205
OR YOU WOULD BE IN A DITCH
FOR DAYS, AND THEN SUDDENLY

00:23:44.205 --> 00:23:49.410
YOU WERE TOLD, "GET UP
AND WALK ACROSS THAT FIELD."

00:23:52.013 --> 00:23:55.917
Osgood:
THE WAR LASTS LONGER
THAN ANYONE HAD ANTICIPATED.

00:23:58.953 --> 00:24:03.724
DAYS BECOME MONTHS,
AND MONTHS STRETCH IN

00:24:07.628 --> 00:24:10.231
THE HUMAN TOLL IS ENORMOUS.

00:24:10.231 --> 00:24:15.002
SOLDIERS WRITE HOME:
"THE SIGHTS WERE AWFUL--

00:24:15.002 --> 00:24:19.340
"DEAD MEN ALL OVER THE PLACE,
SOME HALF-BURIED BY SHELLS.

00:24:19.340 --> 00:24:23.244
"IT WAS SIMPLY A CASE
OF LOOKING DEATH IN THE FACE

00:24:23.244 --> 00:24:26.714
AND WAITING TO BE HIT."

00:24:30.184 --> 00:24:31.052
EARLY IN THE WAR

00:24:31.485 --> 00:24:34.088
AN ENGLISH PSYCHOLOGIST
NAMED CHARLES MEYERS--

00:24:34.088 --> 00:24:35.823
BASED AT THE FRONT--

00:24:35.823 --> 00:24:38.859
REPORTS SEEING SOLDIERS
COME OUT OF THEIR TRENCHES

00:24:38.859 --> 00:24:41.462
WITH MYSTERIOUS SYMPTOMS.

00:24:41.462 --> 00:24:45.800
HE THINKS THE CAUSE MAY BE
A POISON GAS OR CHEMICALS--

00:24:45.800 --> 00:24:50.137
ALL OF WHICH ARE TESTED FOR
TO NO AVAIL.

00:24:50.137 --> 00:24:54.475
DOCTORS SEE SOLDIERS
WITH UNEXPLAINED TREMORS;

00:24:54.475 --> 00:24:57.511
SOME WHO HAVE GONE
BLIND OR DEAF OVERNIGHT;

00:24:57.511 --> 00:25:00.548
OTHERS MUTE, PARALYZED, CRYING.

00:25:00.548 --> 00:25:04.018
MEYERS SPECULATES THAT THESE
BEHAVIORS ARE SOMEHOW RELATED

00:25:04.018 --> 00:25:07.054
TO EXPLODING SHELLS ON THE FRONT

00:25:07.054 --> 00:25:09.223
SO HE CALLS IT "SHELL SHOCK."

00:25:11.392 --> 00:25:13.561
BUT THEN, SOLDIERS WHO
HAVE YET TO SEE COMBAT

00:25:13.561 --> 00:25:17.465
APPEAR WITH SIMILAR SYMPTOMS.

00:25:17.465 --> 00:25:19.633
Roth:
SHELL SHOCK, IN MANY WAYS

00:25:20.067 --> 00:25:22.670
RESEMBLED
THE SYMPTOMS OF HYSTERIA.

00:25:22.670 --> 00:25:24.839
THAT WAS VERY EMBARRASSING.

00:25:24.839 --> 00:25:27.441
HYSTERIA WAS SOMETHING
THAT HAPPENED TO WOMEN.

00:25:27.441 --> 00:25:31.345
EVEN THOUGH THE 19th CENTURY
SAW THEORIES THAT SHOWED

00:25:31.345 --> 00:25:33.948
THAT MEN COULD
BE HYSTERICS, TOO

00:25:33.948 --> 00:25:35.683
THE CRUMBLING OF THE PSYCHE

00:25:36.117 --> 00:25:40.021
WAS THOUGHT TO BE SOMETHING
THAT WOMEN WERE PRONE TO.

00:25:40.021 --> 00:25:44.792
THIS WAS SEXIST,
EVEN MISOGYNISTIC SCIENCE.

00:25:49.563 --> 00:25:52.166
DOCTORS TRIED TO FIND
ANOTHER NAME FOR IT

00:25:52.166 --> 00:25:54.769
SO AS TO SPARE THEIR SOLDIERS

00:25:54.769 --> 00:25:57.805
THE SHAME OF BEING
CALLED HYSTERICS.

00:25:57.805 --> 00:26:01.709
Showalter:
THEY ABSOLUTELY COULDN'T BELIEVE
THAT MEN COULD BE HYSTERICAL

00:26:01.709 --> 00:26:04.311
AND WHEN THEY BEGAN
TO SEE THE SYMPTOMS IN MEN

00:26:04.311 --> 00:26:06.914
ALL THE DOCTORS SAID,
"THIS LOOKS LIKE HYSTERIA."

00:26:06.914 --> 00:26:08.215
BUT AT SOME LEVEL

00:26:08.215 --> 00:26:11.252
THEY WOULD NOT ALLOW
THEMSELVES TO BELIEVE IT.

00:26:15.589 --> 00:26:17.324
Osgood:
"WAR NEUROSIS"

00:26:17.324 --> 00:26:19.493
"BURIED-ALIVE NEUROSIS"

00:26:19.493 --> 00:26:21.228
"SOLDIER'S HEART"--

00:26:21.228 --> 00:26:24.698
ALL NAMES TO DESCRIBE
MALE HYSTERIA.

00:26:24.698 --> 00:26:27.301
SOME 80,000 SOLDIERS
WOULD SUCCUMB

00:26:27.301 --> 00:26:29.470
DURING THE COURSE OF THE WAR.

00:26:31.639 --> 00:26:33.808
MILITARY DOCTORS LOOK
LONG AND HARD

00:26:33.808 --> 00:26:36.410
FOR A PHYSICAL EXPLANATION
FOR THE SYMPTOMS;

00:26:36.844 --> 00:26:39.880
DENCE OF DAMAGE
FOR A PHYSICAL EXPLANATION
TO THE NERVOUS SYSTEM;E EVI

00:26:39.880 --> 00:26:43.784
FOR EVIDENCE OF
TAINTED HEREDITY.

00:26:43.784 --> 00:26:47.688
THEY WERE SO PERSUADED THAT
THERE HAD TO BE AN ORGANIC CAUSE

00:26:48.122 --> 00:26:52.026
AND IN SOME WAYS, SO PREJUDICED
AGAINST A PSYCHOLOGICAL CAUSE

00:26:52.026 --> 00:26:53.327
THAT AS THEY ELIMINATED

00:26:53.327 --> 00:26:56.363
AND ELIMINATED AND ELIMINATED
POSSIBLE SOURCES

00:26:56.363 --> 00:26:58.532
THEY JUST CONTINUED TO LOOK.

00:27:02.436 --> 00:27:06.340
THE ONLY EXPLANATION LEFT
IS COWARDICE.

00:27:06.340 --> 00:27:10.244
TO MANY OFFICERS,
THESE SOLDIERS ARE MALINGERERS

00:27:10.244 --> 00:27:15.449
WHO SHOULD BE TRIED,
COURT-MARTIALED AND EXECUTED.

00:27:15.449 --> 00:27:18.486
AND IN FACT, SOME ARE.

00:27:21.088 --> 00:27:24.125
BUT AMONG DOCTORS,
THERE ARE A PIONEERING FEW

00:27:24.125 --> 00:27:26.293
FAMILIAR WITH FREUD'S THEORIES

00:27:26.293 --> 00:27:28.896
WHO BELIEVE THAT SHELL SHOCK
IS PSYCHOLOGICAL.

00:27:29.330 --> 00:27:32.800
FOR THEM, THE WAR OFFERS
AN UNUSUAL OPPORTUNITY.

00:27:32.800 --> 00:27:36.270
Showalter:
FREUD HAD WORKED WITH A VERY
SMALL NUMBER OF PATIENTS

00:27:36.270 --> 00:27:38.439
AND WITH WOMEN PATIENTS WHO CAME

00:27:38.439 --> 00:27:41.475
FROM QUITE A LIMITED
SEGMENT OF VIENNESE SOCIETY--

00:27:41.475 --> 00:27:44.512
UPPER-MIDDLE-CLASS WOMEN FROM
JEWISH FAMILIES BASICALLY

00:27:44.945 --> 00:27:47.548
WHO WERE LEADING LIVES
OF BOREDOM AND LEISURE.

00:27:47.548 --> 00:27:50.151
AND SUDDENLY
HERE YOU HAVE THE WAR--

00:27:50.151 --> 00:27:53.621
80,000 SHELL-SHOCK CASES
IN THE EUROPEAN ARMIES.

00:27:53.621 --> 00:27:56.223
SO THEY PROVIDED
AN EXTRAORDINARY WEALTH

00:27:56.223 --> 00:27:58.826
OF EXPERIMENTAL MATERIAL,
SO TO SPEAK

00:27:58.826 --> 00:28:01.862
AND DOCTORS, AT THE SAME TIME
THAT THEY WERE APPALLED

00:28:01.862 --> 00:28:03.597
WERE FASCINATED.

00:28:04.031 --> 00:28:06.574
THEY RECOGNIZED THE OPPORTUNITY
THEY HAD BEFORE THEM

00:28:06.574 --> 00:28:07.935
TO STUDY PRECISELY

00:28:07.935 --> 00:28:12.273
THE KINDS OF CONFLICTS
THAT FREUD HAD WRITTEN ABOUT

00:28:12.273 --> 00:28:16.177
IN THIS VERY, VERY LARGE
SAMPLE OF THE POPULATION.

00:28:23.551 --> 00:28:25.719
Harrington:
WE MIGHT BE ABLE TO UNDERSTAND

00:28:25.719 --> 00:28:27.454
WHAT WAS HAPPENING
PSYCHOLOGICALLY

00:28:27.454 --> 00:28:29.190
TO THESE YOUNG MEN
IN THE TRENCHES

00:28:29.623 --> 00:28:32.226
THAT WERE CAUSING THEM
TO DEVELOP THESE SYMPTOMS.

00:28:32.226 --> 00:28:33.961
EVERYTHING IN YOUR BODY
IS SAYING

00:28:33.961 --> 00:28:35.696
"GET OUT OF THERE;
SAVE YOURSELF"

00:28:36.130 --> 00:28:38.299
AND EVERYTHING
IN YOUR TRAINING IS SAYING

00:28:38.299 --> 00:28:40.467
"YOU'VE GOT TO STAY
IN THE TRENCHES

00:28:40.467 --> 00:28:43.938
AND DEFEND YOUR COUNTRY," AND
THE CONFLICT IS SO UNBEARABLE

00:28:43.938 --> 00:28:46.540
THAT AS THE PSYCHOANALYSTS
WOULD ULTIMATELY SAY

00:28:46.540 --> 00:28:50.010
THE ORGANISM TAKES
A FLIGHT INTO ILLNESS.

00:28:56.951 --> 00:29:00.421
Showalter:
SHELL SHOCK IS THE BODY LANGUAGE
OF POWERLESSNESS

00:29:00.421 --> 00:29:06.493
AND POWERLESSNESS CAN COME IN
A LOT OF DIFFERENT SITUATIONS.

00:29:06.493 --> 00:29:09.006
YOU CAN HAVE POWER IN THE WORLD

00:29:12.132 --> 00:29:15.603
WHERE YOU ARE POWERLESS,
FOR A VARIETY OF REASONS

00:29:15.603 --> 00:29:17.771
TO SPEAK YOUR REAL FEELINGS

00:29:17.771 --> 00:29:21.675
THE BODY WILL CONVERT
THOSE FEELINGS INTO SYMPTOMS.

00:29:21.675 --> 00:29:26.447
THESE SOLDIERS,
WHO WERE BRAVE, WHO WERE FIT

00:29:26.880 --> 00:29:32.086
WHO WERE PATRIOTIC,
FOUND THEMSELVES DEALING WITH

00:29:32.086 --> 00:29:37.725
FEAR, ANXIETY, GRIEF,
LONELINESS, DISORIENTATION

00:29:37.725 --> 00:29:41.195
AND ALL THESE KINDS OF FEELINGS
WHICH WERE NEW TO THEM

00:29:41.195 --> 00:29:44.665
AND WHICH WERE NOT
PART OF THE SOCIETY'S DEFINITION

00:29:44.665 --> 00:29:46.400
OF WHAT IT MEANT TO BE A MAN.

00:29:46.400 --> 00:29:49.003
THEY COULDN'T ARTICULATE
THOSE FEELINGS.

00:29:57.678 --> 00:29:59.847
Osgood:
DOCTORS TRY ANY METHOD--

00:29:59.847 --> 00:30:03.317
FROM CRUDE FORMS OF ELECTRIC
SHOCK TO TALKING THERAPY--

00:30:03.317 --> 00:30:05.919
TO RESTORE THE SOLDIER
TO FIGHTING SHAPE

00:30:05.919 --> 00:30:08.088
AND BACK TO THE FRONT.

00:30:12.426 --> 00:30:15.462
FOR THOUSANDS
OF SOLDIERS LIKE THESE

00:30:15.462 --> 00:30:20.668
IT IS THE TALKING CURE THAT
WORKS WHEN NOTHING ELSE DOES.

00:30:20.668 --> 00:30:23.704
SIMPLY TALKING CAN SAVE THEM.

00:30:25.439 --> 00:30:29.777
MANY SOLDIERS FROZEN IN FEAR
CAN NOW BE HEALED.

00:30:38.018 --> 00:30:42.356
SOLDIERS IMMOBILIZED
BY MEMORIES CAN NOW MOVE ON.

00:30:52.333 --> 00:30:54.501
THE LABORATORY OF WAR

00:30:54.501 --> 00:30:56.622
DEMONSTRATES THAT MANY
OF FREUD'S IDEAS

00:30:56.622 --> 00:30:59.273
ARE MORE THAN ABSTRACT THEORIES;

00:30:59.273 --> 00:31:04.398
THEY CAN OFFER
A PRACTICAL BASIS FOR TREATMENT.

00:31:07.948 --> 00:31:10.984
ABOUT THE HIDDEN SOURCES
OF HUMAN BEHAVIOR

00:31:10.984 --> 00:31:14.021
FOR DECADES TO COME.

00:31:14.021 --> 00:31:16.190
I THINK IT SHOWED UP
TO PEOPLE ON A MASSIVE SCALE

00:31:16.623 --> 00:31:22.262
THAT EMOTIONAL AND ENVIRONMENTAL
FACTORS WERE EXTREMELY IMPORTANT

00:31:22.262 --> 00:31:26.600
IN DETERMINING OUR MENTAL LIVES.

00:31:28.335 --> 00:31:31.372
IT'S AS AN EXPERIENCE OF THE WAR

00:31:31.805 --> 00:31:34.842
THAT PSYCHOLOGY AND PSYCHIATRY

00:31:34.842 --> 00:31:38.746
NOW CEASE BEING
SIMPLY MEDICAL SPECIALTIES

00:31:38.746 --> 00:31:41.782
APPLIED TO A VERY
TINY NUMBER OF PEOPLE

00:31:41.782 --> 00:31:45.686
BUT A WAY TO UNDERSTAND,
IN GENERAL

00:31:45.686 --> 00:31:49.156
OURSELVES, OUR MINDS
AND OUR WORLD.

00:32:05.205 --> 00:32:07.374
WHEN WORLD WAR I
COMES TO A CLOSE

00:32:07.374 --> 00:32:09.543
A BATTLE OF
A DIFFERENT SORT BEGINS

00:32:09.543 --> 00:32:12.146
ONLY THIS TIME
THE WEAPONS ARE WORDS

00:32:12.146 --> 00:32:14.314
AND THE SOLDIERS ARE SCIENTISTS.

00:32:14.314 --> 00:32:16.049
THIS NEW BATTLE WILL RAGE

00:32:16.049 --> 00:32:19.953
BETWEEN TWO DIAMETRICALLY
OPPOSED VIEWS OF HUMAN BEHAVIOR.

00:32:19.953 --> 00:32:22.990
ON ONE SIDE ARE THE SCIENTISTS
WHO SEE OUR PERSONALITIES

00:32:22.990 --> 00:32:27.327
AS UNCHANGING, FIXED AT BIRTH,
BIOLOGICALLY DETERMINED.

00:32:27.327 --> 00:32:30.364
AND ON THE OTHER SIDE ARE
THOSE WHO BELIEVE WE CAN CHANGE

00:32:30.364 --> 00:32:32.966
THAT WE ARE INFLUENCED
BY OUR EXPERIENCES

00:32:32.966 --> 00:32:35.569
AND WHAT WE LEARN ALONG THE WAY.

00:32:35.569 --> 00:32:38.172
WHEN THE DEBATE HEATS UP
IN THE UNITED STATES

00:32:38.172 --> 00:32:40.774
LIFE IS CHANGING RAPIDLY
AND DRAMATICALLY.

00:32:40.774 --> 00:32:43.377
IT'S AN UNSETTLING TIME
FOR MOST PEOPLE.

00:32:43.377 --> 00:32:46.413
WE YEARN FOR STABILITY
AND NORMALCY AND CERTAINTY.

00:32:46.413 --> 00:32:49.450
WHAT SCIENTISTS HAVE TO SAY
ABOUT HUMAN BEHAVIOR--

00:32:49.450 --> 00:32:52.052
WHETHER IT'S FIXED AT BIRTH
AND PREDICTABLE

00:32:52.052 --> 00:32:55.088
OR SHAPED BY THE ENVIRONMENT
AND CHANGEABLE--

00:32:55.088 --> 00:32:58.559
WILL HAVE A PROFOUND EFFECT
ON HOW PEOPLE VIEW THE FUTURE

00:32:58.559 --> 00:33:02.463
HOW THEY SEE EACH OTHER, AND
EVEN HOW THEY LIVE THEIR LIVES.

00:33:05.499 --> 00:33:09.837
Osgood:
IN 1918, THE WAR TO END ALL WARS
IS FINALLY OVER.

00:33:12.005 --> 00:33:15.476
AMERICAN SOLDIERS RETURN TO A
COUNTRY EAGER TO TAKE ITS PLACE

00:33:15.476 --> 00:33:18.078
AS A LEADER
IN A RAPIDLY CHANGING WORLD.

00:33:20.247 --> 00:33:24.585
BUT AMERICA'S OPTIMISTIC HOPES
FOR THE FUTURE ARE SOON UNDERCUT

00:33:24.585 --> 00:33:27.187
BY SOME UNEXPECTED
AND DISTURBING NEWS.

00:33:27.187 --> 00:33:30.657
THE ARMY PUBLISHES
THE RESULTS OF TESTS

00:33:30.657 --> 00:33:32.826
IT CONDUCTED DURING WARTIME

00:33:32.826 --> 00:33:36.730
ASSESSING THE MENTAL CAPACITY
OF ITS RECRUITS.

00:33:36.730 --> 00:33:38.899
USION:
ASSESSING THE MENTAL CAPACITY
OF ITS RECRUITS.NG CONCL

00:33:38.899 --> 00:33:43.237
NEARLY HALF OF ALL AMERICAN
SOLDIERS ARE FEEBLEMINDED.

00:33:43.237 --> 00:33:46.273
ARMY PSYCHOLOGISTS
HAVE FIRED THE FIRST SHOT

00:33:46.273 --> 00:33:51.044
ENTIFIC WAR THAT
ARMY PSYCHOLOGISTS
WILL LE.IRED THE FIRST SHOT SCI

00:33:51.044 --> 00:33:56.683
WHEN THE ARMY TESTS RESULTS WERE
PUBLISHED, AND IT WAS STATED

00:33:56.683 --> 00:34:01.455
THAT A GOODLY PORTION OF
INDUCTEES INTO THE U.S. ARMY

00:34:01.455 --> 00:34:04.057
HAD A MENTAL AGE OF UNDER 12--

00:34:04.057 --> 00:34:09.263
ERGO, MORON BY POPULAR
DEFINITION OF PSYCHOLOGISTS--

00:34:09.696 --> 00:34:11.865
THERE WAS A SENSE OF SHOCK.

00:34:11.865 --> 00:34:15.769
HOW COULD IT BE
THAT SO MANY AMERICAN BOYS

00:34:15.769 --> 00:34:17.938
HAD SUCH LOW INTELLIGENCE?

00:34:17.938 --> 00:34:23.577
THEY LED PEOPLE TO BELIEVE
THAT WE HAD A MAJOR PROBLEM

00:34:23.577 --> 00:34:26.613
NAMELY, WE HAD TOO MANY MORONS;

00:34:26.613 --> 00:34:30.083
THE COUNTRY WAS FILLED
WITH MORONS.

00:34:30.083 --> 00:34:33.120
THE THEORY THAT
THE ARMY TESTS HAVE PROVEN

00:34:33.120 --> 00:34:37.457
THAT THE COUNTRY IS REALLY
A LOT DUMBER THAN PEOPLE THOUGHT

00:34:37.457 --> 00:34:40.060
IS GOING TO FEED INTO
A LOT OF FEARS

00:34:42.663 --> 00:34:44.831
Osgood:
THE FEARS MU

00:34:44.831 --> 00:34:47.434
THE FEAR THAT
AMERICA'S GENE POOL

00:34:47.434 --> 00:34:50.904
IS BEING WEAKENED BY AN UNENDING
INFLUX OF IMMIGRANTS;

00:34:50.904 --> 00:34:54.808
THE HAT AMERICANS WILL
LACK THE MENTAL FACULTIES

00:34:54.808 --> 00:34:57.844
TO PERFORM THE COMPLEX TASKS
OF MODERN LIFE.

00:35:00.447 --> 00:35:03.483
WHEN THE ARMY COMMISSIONED
THE TESTS DURING THE WAR

00:35:03.483 --> 00:35:06.520
THE GENERALS FACED
A STAGGERING LOGISTICAL TASK.

00:35:06.520 --> 00:35:09.122
DELUGED WITH SOME
TWO MILLION RECRUITS

00:35:09.556 --> 00:35:11.725
THEY TRIED TO MATCH
EACH MAN TO THE JOB

00:35:12.159 --> 00:35:16.063
CHOOSING POTENTIAL OFFICERS AND
WEEDING OUT POTENTIAL MISFITS.

00:35:18.231 --> 00:35:22.030
IN DESPERATION, THE ARMY TURNED
TO A GROUP OF PSYCHOLOGISTS

00:35:24.738 --> 00:35:30.377
TO GET THE JOB DONE: A
STANDARDIZED INTELLIGENCE TEST.

00:35:30.811 --> 00:35:35.148
HENRY GODDARD, FATHER OF THE
FIRST AMERICAN INTELLIGENCE TEST

00:35:35.148 --> 00:35:38.185
IS PART OF A NEW WAVE
OF PSYCHOLOGISTS

00:35:38.185 --> 00:35:41.221
EAGER TO BE OF SERVICE
TO THEIR COUNTRY.

00:35:41.221 --> 00:35:45.993
Zenderland:
THEY HAD ONE CLEAR, PRACTICAL
GOAL FOR THEIR SCIENCE--

00:35:45.993 --> 00:35:49.029
TO SORT THE ENTIRE ARMY,
QUICKLY, IN AN HOUR.

00:35:49.029 --> 00:35:52.933
THEY HAD TO FIND A TEST
THAT COULD BE DONE FAST

00:35:52.933 --> 00:35:55.535
AND THAT COULD
IMMEDIATELY DISTINGUISH

00:35:55.535 --> 00:35:58.138
DIFFERENT LEVELS
OF MENTAL SKILL.

00:35:58.138 --> 00:36:00.741
Osgood:
THEY SPRING INTO ACTION.

00:36:00.741 --> 00:36:04.645
THEY TEST GENERAL KNOWLEDGE
WITH QUESTIONS LIKE:

00:36:04.645 --> 00:36:06.813
"WHAT IS CRISCO?"

00:36:06.813 --> 00:36:09.850
"WHAT IS THE PRODUCT
ADVERTISED BY VELVET JOE?"

00:36:09.850 --> 00:36:12.019
OR "WHAT IS A DIBBLE?"

00:36:12.019 --> 00:36:14.187
Zenderland:
THE ARMY TESTS REQUIRED

00:36:14.187 --> 00:36:16.790
AN IMMENSE AMOUNT
OF CULTURAL INFORMATION.

00:36:16.790 --> 00:36:18.959
ONE HAD TO KNOW AMERICAN SPORTS

00:36:18.959 --> 00:36:21.561
ONE HAD TO KNOW
AMERICAN ADVERTISING

00:36:21.561 --> 00:36:23.730
ONE HAD TO KNOW THAT VELVET JOE

00:36:23.730 --> 00:36:26.333
WAS A CHARACTER
WHO ADVERTISED TOBACCO.

00:36:26.333 --> 00:36:31.972
Osgood:
IN ADDITION, THEY ALSO ASK
QUESTIONS OF PRACTICAL JUDGMENT:

00:36:32.406 --> 00:36:35.008
"IS BLACK THE SAME AS WHITE?"

00:36:35.008 --> 00:36:38.912
AND "WHY IS BEEF
BETTER FOOD THAN CABBAGE?"

00:36:38.912 --> 00:36:42.816
THE INHERENT FALLACY, CERTAINLY
OF THE TESTS OF THOSE DAYS

00:36:42.816 --> 00:36:44.551
WAS THE FACT THEY WERE FILLED

00:36:44.985 --> 00:36:49.756
WITH THE CULTURE OF
A PARTICULAR CLASS AND LOCATION

00:36:49.756 --> 00:36:53.226
AND WERE TREATED AS THOUGH
THEY WERE UNIVERSAL AND FAIR.

00:36:53.226 --> 00:36:56.697
AND PEOPLE WHO WERE
NOT FROM THOSE CLASSES OR GROUPS

00:36:56.697 --> 00:36:57.564
DID NOT DO WELL.

00:37:02.769 --> 00:37:07.107
NATIVE, INBORN INTELLIGENCE,
NOT ACQUIRED KNOWLEDGE...

00:37:08.842 --> 00:37:14.047
AND THIS INTELLIGENCE SHOULD BE
AS MEASURABLE AS A BAR OF STEEL.

00:37:14.047 --> 00:37:16.216
Man:
IT WAS BELIEVED THAT THERE WAS

00:37:16.216 --> 00:37:18.385
AN ENTITY CALLED INTELLIGENCE

00:37:18.385 --> 00:37:20.554
AND THAT TESTS WERE MEASURING IT

00:37:20.554 --> 00:37:23.590
IN THE SAME WAY THAT THERE'S
AN ENTITY CALLED POTATOES--

00:37:23.590 --> 00:37:25.759
WHEN YOU PUT THEM ON A SCALE

00:37:26.193 --> 00:37:28.361
THERE'S A SCALE
THAT'S MEASURING THEM.

00:37:28.361 --> 00:37:32.699
Narrator:
THE SCALE FOR INTELLIGENCE
IS DEVELOPED BY HENRY GODDARD

00:37:32.699 --> 00:37:36.603
AT THE TRAINING SCHOOL FOR
FEEBLEMINDED BOYS AND GIRLS

00:37:36.603 --> 00:37:38.772
IN VINELAND, NEW JERSEY.

00:37:41.374 --> 00:37:43.977
THROUGH HIS OBSERVATIONS,
HE COMES TO BELIEVE

00:37:43.977 --> 00:37:47.447
THAT INTELLIGENCE-- AND ITS
OPPOSITE, FEEBLEMINDEDNESS--

00:37:47.447 --> 00:37:50.917
IS INHERITED.

00:37:50.917 --> 00:37:53.954
BUT AS A SCIENTIST,
GODDARD WANTS PROOF.

00:37:53.954 --> 00:37:56.990
HE CONFESSES TO HIS FRIEND,
CHARLES DAVENPORT:

00:37:57.424 --> 00:38:00.894
"WHEN IT COMES TO
THE GENETICS OF INTELLIGENCE

00:38:00.894 --> 00:38:03.930
I HAVE MUCH MORE ZEAL
THAN KNOWLEDGE."

00:38:06.533 --> 00:38:09.136
CHARLES DAVENPORT IS A PIONEER

00:38:09.569 --> 00:38:11.738
FIELD
CHARLES DOF GENETICS.A PIONEERG

00:38:11.738 --> 00:38:14.775
HE, TOO, BELIKE INTELLIGENC
E

00:38:14.775 --> 00:38:21.715
CAN BE PASSED DOWN
FROM ONE GENERATION TO THE NEXT.

00:38:21.715 --> 00:38:24.751
IF, AS THE EXPERIMENTS
OF GREGOR MENDEL HAVE SHOWN

00:38:24.751 --> 00:38:28.655
E GENE FOR WRINKLED
IF, AS THE EXPERIMENTS
PEAS AND ANOTHER FOR SMOOTH ON

00:38:28.655 --> 00:38:31.258
ONE GENE FOR BLUE EYES
AND ANOTHER FOR BROWN

00:38:31.691 --> 00:38:34.728
THEN PERHAPS THERE ARE
ALSO GENES FOR OTHER TRAITS

00:38:34.728 --> 00:38:37.330
LIKE INTELLIGENCE.

00:38:40.367 --> 00:38:46.006
A RESPECTED BIOLOGIST FRF CHI
CAGO

00:38:46.006 --> 00:38:51.645
THE HEREDITY TRAITS OF ANIMALS--
CHICKENS, CANARIES AND RABBITS.

00:38:54.247 --> 00:38:57.284
THROUGH HIS RESEARCH,
DAVENPORT BECOMES CONVINCED

00:38:57.284 --> 00:38:59.886
THAT MENDELIAN GENETICS
WILL EXPLAIN

00:38:59.886 --> 00:39:02.923
N
IN PLANTS AND ANIMALS

00:39:02.923 --> 00:39:06.393
BUT ALSO IN HUMAN BEINGS.

00:39:06.393 --> 00:39:08.995
Man:
THEY TRIED TO FIND
BIOLOGICAL BASES

00:39:08.995 --> 00:39:10.730
OF THINGS
THAT THEY CALLED NOMADISM--

00:39:10.730 --> 00:39:12.899
THE TENDENCY OF PEOPLE
TO MOVE FROM PLACE TO PLACE.

00:39:12.899 --> 00:39:15.936
AND AT LEAST ONE GENETICIST
FOUND A GENETIC BASIS

00:39:15.936 --> 00:39:19.840
FOR WHAT HE CALLED
THALASSOPHILIA, LOVE OF THE SEA

00:39:19.840 --> 00:39:21.575
THAT WAS EXPRESSED
IN NAVAL OFFICERS

00:39:22.008 --> 00:39:24.177
AND WHICH HE CONTENDED
MUST BE A SEX-LINKED TRAIT--

00:39:24.177 --> 00:39:25.478
THAT IS, TO MALES--

00:39:25.478 --> 00:39:28.515
BECAUSE ONLY MALES
BECAME OFFICERS IN THE NAVY.

00:39:28.949 --> 00:39:33.720
Narrator:
AND DAVENPORT BELIEVES THAT
OTHER TRAITS ARE LINKED, TOO.

00:39:33.720 --> 00:39:36.323
HE BELIEVES
THAT LOW INTELLIGENCE

00:39:36.323 --> 00:39:39.793
CAUSES POVERTY, CRIMINALITY
AND PROSTITUTION

00:39:39.793 --> 00:39:42.395
AND IF INTELLIGENCE
IS FIXED AT BIRTH

00:39:42.829 --> 00:39:47.167
THEN THESE BEHAVIORS MUST BE
GENETIC IN ORIGIN AS WELL.

00:39:50.637 --> 00:39:53.673
THE TRAITS WERE BELIEVED
TO BE UNCHANGEABLE.

00:39:53.673 --> 00:39:56.276
WE HAD, AS A MATTER OF FACT,
THE PHRASE:

00:39:56.276 --> 00:39:59.312
"THE LEOPARD CANNOT
CHANGE HIS SPOTS."

00:39:59.312 --> 00:40:01.481
THEREFORE,
PEOPLE CANNOT CHANGE

00:40:01.481 --> 00:40:03.650
WHAT WAS GIVEN TO THEM
BY NATURE.

00:40:03.650 --> 00:40:06.253
THERE WAS A BELIEF
WE WERE PRODUCTS OF NATURE

00:40:06.253 --> 00:40:08.855
PREDESTINED TO BE
WHAT WE WERE BORN

00:40:08.855 --> 00:40:12.759
AND THAT ENVIRONMENT
HAD NO EFFECT ON IT.

00:40:16.229 --> 00:40:19.699
Osgood:
DAVENPORT'S IDEAS CATCH FIRE
AMONG THOSE

00:40:19.699 --> 00:40:22.736
LOOKING FOR SCIENTIFIC WAYS
TO IMPROVE SOCIETY.

00:40:24.905 --> 00:40:27.941
HE RECRUITS GRADUATES
OF VASSAR AND HARVARD

00:40:27.941 --> 00:40:32.279
EAGER TO JOIN HIM ON THE
VARESEARCH.

00:40:32.279 --> 00:40:36.616
HE PERSUADES THE CARNEGIE
INSTITUTION OF WASHINGTON

00:40:36.616 --> 00:40:41.821
TO FUND A NEW RESEARCH STATION
IN COLD SPRING HARBOR, NEW YORK.

00:40:43.556 --> 00:40:45.725
ALL FOR THE PROMOTION
OF EUGENICS

00:40:45.725 --> 00:40:49.629
A MOVEMENT TO IMPROVE
THE QUALITY OF THE HUMAN RACE

00:40:49.629 --> 00:40:52.232
BY SELECTIVE BREEDING.

00:40:56.910 --> 00:41:01.341
BUT NOT EVERYONE BELIEVES
THAT BIOLOGY IS DESTINY.

00:41:01.341 --> 00:41:06.112
FOR MANY SCIENTISTS, IT'S YOUR
EXPERIENCES IN LIFE THAT COUNT--

00:41:06.112 --> 00:41:10.016
YOUR UPBRINGING, YOUR EDUCATION,
UR ENVIRONMENT.

00:41:10.016 --> 00:41:14.354
CHIEF AMONG THESE SCIENTISTS
IS PSYCHOLOGIST JOHN WATSON

00:41:14.354 --> 00:41:19.125
WHO OFFERS A THEORY THAT IS
THE MIRROR OPPOSITE OF EUGENICS.

00:41:19.125 --> 00:41:23.463
THIS WAS THE HEYDAY OF
HEREDITARIANS AND GENETICISTS

00:41:23.463 --> 00:41:25.632
WHO SAID THAT HUMAN BEINGS

00:41:25.632 --> 00:41:30.837
WERE CONSTRAINED BY THEIR
GENETIC INHERITANCE.

00:41:31.271 --> 00:41:33.440
AND WATSON WAS SAYING
THAT THIS IS BALONEY;

00:41:33.440 --> 00:41:39.079
THAT HUMAN BEINGS WERE SHAPED
SOLELY BY THEIR ENVIRONMENT.

00:41:41.247 --> 00:41:44.718
Osgood:
OVER THE YEARS, WATSON STUDIES
THE BEHAVIOR OF BABIES--

00:41:44.718 --> 00:41:46.886
HUNDREDS OF THEM.

00:41:49.489 --> 00:41:52.959
TO WATSON, WE ARRIVE
IN THE WORLD A BLANK SLATE--

00:41:52.959 --> 00:41:55.128
TABULA RASA.

00:41:55.128 --> 00:41:56.863
NEARLY EVERYTHING IS LEARNED

00:41:57.297 --> 00:42:01.201
EVEN THINGS WE THINK
ARE INSTINCTUAL, LIKE FEAR.

00:42:03.370 --> 00:42:07.273
TO PROVE THAT ENVIRONMENT
IS MORE POWERFUL THA

00:42:07.273 --> 00:42:09.442
WATSON DESIGNS AN EXPERIMENT

00:42:09.442 --> 00:42:12.479
FOR AN INFANT KNOWN AS
LITTLE ALBERT.

00:42:12.479 --> 00:42:15.949
HE'S SO CONFIDENT,
HE FILMS IT FOR POSTERITY.

00:42:18.551 --> 00:42:20.720
AT FIRST,
ALBERT SHOWS LITTLE FEAR

00:42:20.720 --> 00:42:23.757
EVEN WHEN WATSON PLACES
A BURNING NEWSPAPER

00:42:23.757 --> 00:42:25.925
IN FRONT OF HIM.

00:42:28.094 --> 00:42:31.998
ALBERT IS ALSO UNAFRAID
WHEN HE ENCOUNTERS A WHITE RAT

00:42:32.432 --> 00:42:34.601
FOR THE FIRST TIME IN HIS LIFE.

00:42:34.601 --> 00:42:37.203
BUT THEN WATSON
SHOWS ALBERT THE RAT

00:42:37.203 --> 00:42:39.806
ACCOMPANIED
BY A LOUD CLANGING NOISE--

00:42:39.806 --> 00:42:42.842
ONE OF THE FEW THINGS THAT
UPSETS LITTLE ALBERT.

00:42:42.842 --> 00:42:45.879
(cries)

00:42:45.879 --> 00:42:47.614
AND HE DOES IT AGAIN...

00:42:47.614 --> 00:42:49.349
(cries)

00:42:49.349 --> 00:42:50.650
N.

00:42:50.650 --> 00:42:52.819
(loud clanging)

00:42:52.819 --> 00:42:56.723
EVENTUALLY, ALBERT LEARNS
TO FEAR NOT JUST THE RAT

00:42:56.723 --> 00:43:00.627
BUT ALL FURRY THINGS,
EVEN WITHOUT THE LOUD NOISE.

00:43:00.627 --> 00:43:05.832
IN WATSON'S MIND, THE LITTLE
ALBERT EXPERIMENT IS A SUCCESS

00:43:05.832 --> 00:43:10.603
BECAUSE IT PROVES THAT FEARS
ARE LEARNED, NOT INHERITED.

00:43:10.603 --> 00:43:13.206
WATSON CALLS
HIS THEORY "BEHAVIORISM"

00:43:13.206 --> 00:43:14.941
AND BEGINS TO POPULARIZE IT.

00:43:15.375 --> 00:43:17.977
HE URGES PARENTS
TO TAKE ACTIVE CONTROL

00:43:17.977 --> 00:43:20.580
OF THEIR CHILDREN'S UPBRINGING

00:43:20.580 --> 00:43:24.484
BY SHAPING THEIR ENVIRONMENT...

00:43:24.484 --> 00:43:28.388
TO THINK OF THE HOME
AS A SCIENTIFIC LABORATORY.

00:43:31.424 --> 00:43:33.593
ATSON'S
TO THINK OF THE HOME
AS INTEREST IN CHILDHOODRY.T W

00:43:33.593 --> 00:43:35.328
IS PURELY PROFESSIONAL.

00:43:35.762 --> 00:43:37.497
Maher:
HE DIDN'T LIKE CHILDREN MUCH.

00:43:37.931 --> 00:43:40.533
HE REFERRED TO THEM,
IN ONE OF HIS MANY STATEMENTS

00:43:40.533 --> 00:43:43.136
AS ALWAYS SQUALLING
AND SHOUTING AND DIRTY

00:43:43.136 --> 00:43:46.172
AND WANTING TO BE FED
AND SORT OF A NUISANCE.

00:43:46.172 --> 00:43:47.907
IT WAS CLEAR HE DIDN'T
PARTICULARLY LIKE THEM

00:43:47.907 --> 00:43:49.642
IN HIS OWN ENVIRONMENT

00:43:49.642 --> 00:43:52.245
BUT HE FELT
THAT THE GOOD OF SOCIETY

00:43:52.245 --> 00:43:57.884
REQUIRED SHAPING INDIVIDUALS
RIGHT FROM DAY ONE

00:43:57.884 --> 00:43:59.185
YOU HAD TO START
WITH THE BABIES.

00:43:59.185 --> 00:44:01.788
Narrator:
EBULLIENT AND SELF-PROMOTING

00:44:01.788 --> 00:44:05.258
WATSON GATHERS A WIDE
AND APPRECIATIVE AUDIENCE

00:44:05.258 --> 00:44:07.427
WHICH HOLDS IN HIGH ESTEEM

00:44:07.427 --> 00:44:11.331
ANY SCIENTIFIC THINKING
ON THE SUBJECT OF CHILD REARING.

00:44:15.668 --> 00:44:18.705
SCIENCE WAS
INCREASINGLY IMPORTANT

00:44:18.705 --> 00:44:20.874
IN THE POPULAR MIND-SET.

