00:50:37.383 --> 00:50:39.552
BEGIN TO STUDY GENETICS

00:50:39.552 --> 00:50:42.154
WHEN THEY BEGIN TO DISCOVER,
FOR INSTANCE

00:50:42.154 --> 00:50:44.757
THAT EVEN UNDERSTANDING
AN ORGANISM

00:50:44.757 --> 00:50:48.227
AS SIMPLE AS A FRUIT FLY
IS FAR MORE COMPLEX A PROCESS

00:50:48.227 --> 00:50:49.962
THAN WE EVER DREAMED POSSIBLE.

00:50:51.697 --> 00:50:55.167
Osgood:
IN LABORATORIES, LIKE THIS ONE
AT THE UNIVERSITY OF TEXAS

00:50:55.167 --> 00:50:56.469
SCIENTISTS ARE STUDYING

00:50:56.469 --> 00:50:59.071
THE INHERITANCE PATTERNS
OF FRUIT FLIES.

00:51:00.806 --> 00:51:02.542
BECAUSE FRUIT FLIES
BREED QUICKLY

00:51:02.542 --> 00:51:05.144
IT MAKES THEM IDEAL SUBJECTS
FOR EXPERIMENTS

00:51:05.144 --> 00:51:08.180
TO SEE HOW THEY CHANGE.

00:51:08.180 --> 00:51:11.217
BY THE LATE 1920s,
RESEARCH MAKES CLEAR

00:51:11.217 --> 00:51:13.819
THAT GENETICS
WILL NOT BE EXPLAINED

00:51:13.819 --> 00:51:16.856
AS SIMPLY AS
"ONE GENE, ONE TRAIT."

00:51:16.856 --> 00:51:18.591
THE WORK SHOWS THAT MANY TRAITS

00:51:18.591 --> 00:51:20.760
ARE NOT THE PRODUCT
OF SINGLE GENES

00:51:20.760 --> 00:51:25.531
BUT ARE POLYGENIC,
THE PRODUCT OF SEVERAL GENES.

00:51:28.568 --> 00:51:31.604
SOMETHING AS SIMPLE
AS EYE COLOR, FOR EXAMPLE

00:51:31.604 --> 00:51:32.905
CAN BE AFFECTED

00:51:32.905 --> 00:51:36.375
BY AS MANY AS SEVEN
DIFFERENT GENETIC VARIABLES.

00:51:36.375 --> 00:51:38.978
AND IF A FRUIT FLY
IS THIS COMPLEX

00:51:38.978 --> 00:51:42.882
WHAT, SCIENTISTS WONDER, DOES
THAT IMPLY FOR HUMAN GENETICS?

00:51:45.051 --> 00:51:48.521
BUT IN THE PUBLIC'S MIND,
THE SCIENCE OF GENETICS

00:51:48.521 --> 00:51:54.160
THE PSEUDOSCIENCE OF EUGENICS

00:51:54.160 --> 00:51:56.762
TO EXPLAIN HUMAN BEHAVIOR.

