ARE THE MOST POPULAR ADVICE
COLUMNISTS IN THE COUNTRY.

00:59:33.188 --> 00:59:35.357
AMERICANS LOVE ADVICE.

00:59:35.357 --> 00:59:38.393
THEY'RE HELL-BENT
ON SELF-IMPROVEMENT

00:59:38.393 --> 00:59:40.562
OPTIMISTIC ABOUT THEIR PROSPECTS

00:59:40.562 --> 00:59:43.165
AND GUIDED BY
A NEAR-RELIGIOUS BELIEF

00:59:43.165 --> 00:59:46.201
THAT THEY CAN ALWAYS CHANGE
FOR THE BETTER.

00:59:46.201 --> 00:59:50.105
THE OPPOSITE VIEW--
THAT BEHAVIOR IS FIXED AT BIRTH

00:59:50.105 --> 00:59:51.840
AND CAN'T BE CHANGED--

00:59:51.840 --> 00:59:54.443
IS STILL ASSOCIATED
WITH NAZI GERMANY

00:59:54.876 --> 00:59:57.913
WHERE EUGENICS WAS USED
TO JUSTIFY GENOCIDE.

00:59:57.913 --> 01:00:01.383
SO AMERICANS EMBRACE SCIENTISTS
WHO BELIEVE THE OPPOSITE--

01:00:01.383 --> 01:00:05.720
THAT WHEN IT COMES TO IRONMENT T
HAT COUNTS

01:00:05.720 --> 01:00:07.889
AND VIRTUALLY ANYTHING
IS POSSIBLE.

01:00:10.492 --> 01:00:14.396
THESE ARE OPTIMISTIC TIMES
IN 1945.

01:00:14.830 --> 01:00:18.300
THE SOLDIERS WHO FOUGHT AGAINST
TOTALITARIANISM OVERSEAS

01:00:18.300 --> 01:00:21.770
ARE RETURNING HOME TO THE MOST
POWERFUL NATION IN THE WORLD.

01:00:24.806 --> 01:00:27.843
RETURNING TO LIVES
INTERRUPTED...

01:00:27.843 --> 01:00:30.011
TO GIRLFRIENDS...

01:00:30.011 --> 01:00:32.614
TO FAMILIES LEFT BEHIND.

01:00:34.349 --> 01:00:36.952
WITH THE WAR FINALLY OVER
AND VICTORY WON

01:00:36.952 --> 01:00:40.422
ANYTHING, AND EVERYTHING,
SEEMS POSSIBLE.

01:00:40.422 --> 01:00:45.627
Maher:
PEOPLE THOUGHT THAT AFTER
THE STUNNING ACHIEVEMENTS

01:00:45.627 --> 01:00:48.663
OF SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY
IN THE VICTORY OF WORLD WAR II

01:00:48.663 --> 01:00:52.567
THAT THERE WAS, IN PRINCIPLE,
NO LIMIT TO WHAT IT COULD DO

01:00:52.567 --> 01:00:56.037
NOW IN THE INTEREST
OF THE GOOD LIFE AFTER THE WAR.

01:00:56.037 --> 01:00:58.206
THE TECHNOLOGY THAT HAD ALLOWED
US TO WIN THE WAR

01:00:58.640 --> 01:01:01.243
TO DEFEAT HITLER,
TO DEFEAT THE NAZIS

01:01:01.243 --> 01:01:02.544
THIS TECHNOLOGY COULD NOW

01:01:02.544 --> 01:01:05.580
BE PUT INTO THE SERVICE
OF LIBERATING INDIVIDUALS

01:01:06.014 --> 01:01:07.749
OF HELPING THEM
DEVELOP THEMSELVES.

01:01:07.749 --> 01:01:09.484
SO IT WAS A TRANSLATION, I THINK

01:01:09.484 --> 01:01:14.256
OF TECHNOLOGY FROM
AN EMPHASIS ON WEAPONRY

01:01:14.256 --> 01:01:16.858
TO A TECHNOLOGY ON AN EMPHASIS
ON THE HUMAN SPIRIT

01:01:17.292 --> 01:01:19.027
AND THE DEVELOPMENT
OF HUMAN NATURE.

01:01:19.027 --> 01:01:21.196
AND WE COULD TRANSLATE
THAT EXPERTISE

01:01:21.196 --> 01:01:22.931
FROM ONE DOMAIN TO THE OTHER.

01:01:24.666 --> 01:01:28.570
THIS SETUP MAKES
ANY DAY WASH DAY FOR ME.

01:01:30.739 --> 01:01:34.209
AND I CAN DO MY DRYING
IN ANY KIND OF WEATHER.

01:01:35.510 --> 01:01:37.245
Osgood:
BY THE 1950s

01:01:37.245 --> 01:01:39.848
MANY AMERICANS DEVELOP
A NEARLY INSATIABLE APPETITE

01:01:40.282 --> 01:01:42.017
FOR ALL THE NEW THINGS

01:01:42.017 --> 01:01:46.354
THAT CAN BE MANUFACTURED,
BOUGHT, SOLD AND CONSUMED.

01:01:46.354 --> 01:01:49.391
Singer:
WE SEE THE IDEA THAT WE COULD
ENGINEER THE HOUSEHOLD.

01:01:49.391 --> 01:01:51.126
WE COULD ENGINEER THE FAMILY.

01:01:51.126 --> 01:01:53.728
WE COULD ENGINEER ALLOCIETY
.

01:01:58.500 --> 01:02:02.404
Osgood:
WHILE SOME SCIENTISTS ENGINEER
SHINY NEW CONSUMER GOODS

01:02:02.404 --> 01:02:04.139
FOR AN EAGER PUBLIC

01:02:04.139 --> 01:02:07.175
HARVARD PSYCHOLOGIST
B.F. SKINNER SEEKS NOTHING LESS

01:02:07.175 --> 01:02:09.344
THAN THE ENGINEERING
OF HUMAN NATURE.

01:02:12.814 --> 01:02:16.284
IN EXPERIMENTS WITH SUBJECTS
AS SIMPLE AS PIGEONS

01:02:16.284 --> 01:02:20.188
SKINNER DECLARES THAT WITH
THE RIGHT SOCIAL ENGINEERING

01:02:20.188 --> 01:02:23.224
WE CAN CREATE A NEW BREED
OF HUMAN BEING.

01:02:25.393 --> 01:02:28.863
SKINNER IS FIRMLY IN
THE BEHAVIORIST TRADITION

01:02:28.863 --> 01:02:31.466
PIONEERED BY JOHN WATSON
IN THE 1920s.

01:02:31.466 --> 01:02:36.237
LIKE WATSON, SKINNER CONTENDS
THAT WITH THE RIGHT TOOLS

01:02:36.237 --> 01:02:39.274
WE CAN PREDICT
AND CONTROL BEHAVIOR.

01:02:39.274 --> 01:02:41.876
SKINNER REALLY INHERITED
THE MANTLE FROM WATSON

01:02:41.876 --> 01:02:43.564
OF BEHAVIORISM IN THIS COUNTRY

01:02:43.564 --> 01:02:46.214
BUT IT'S KIND OF INTERESTING
TO THINK ABOUT

01:02:46.214 --> 01:02:49.684
HOW THERE'S A SUBTLE DIFFERENCE
IN THE WAY THEY WENT ABOUT IT.

01:02:49.684 --> 01:02:50.986
WATSON, AS WE KNOW

01:02:50.986 --> 01:02:54.022
ENDED UP BECOMING
AN ADVERTISING EXECUTIVE

01:02:54.022 --> 01:02:58.360
ENDED UP EMBRACING THE AMERICAN
VALUE SYSTEM AS IT EXISTED.

01:02:58.360 --> 01:02:59.661
SKINNER WAS DIFFERENT.

01:02:59.661 --> 01:03:00.962
SKINNER WAS A VISIONARY.

01:03:00.962 --> 01:03:03.565
SKINNER FELT THAT
THROUGH BEHAVIORISM

01:03:03.565 --> 01:03:07.035
HE COULD INFLUENCE THE WORLD
TOWARDS A GREATER HUMANITY--

01:03:07.035 --> 01:03:10.939
NOT MEET HUMANITY WHERE IT WAS,
BUT TAKE HUMANITY TO A NEW PLACE

01:03:10.939 --> 01:03:13.108
THROUGH THE PRINCIPLES
OF BEHAVIORISM.

01:03:13.108 --> 01:03:15.710
Osgood:
PICKING UP WHERE
WATSON LEFT OFF

01:03:15.710 --> 01:03:17.879
SKINNER WANTS TO DO
THE RIGOROUS SCIENCE

01:03:17.879 --> 01:03:20.482
TO PROVE THAT ENVIRONMENT
IS EVERYTHING.

01:03:20.482 --> 01:03:22.651
CHANGE THE ENVIRONMENT,
HE ARGUES

01:03:22.651 --> 01:03:24.819
AND YOU CAN CHANGE
THE INDIVIDUAL...

01:03:26.121 --> 01:03:28.289
OR, IN SKINNER'S CASE,
THE PIGEON.

01:03:29.157 --> 01:03:31.326
Maher:
SKINNER HIMSELF

01:03:31.326 --> 01:03:33.495
WAS A BORN GADGETEER.

01:03:33.495 --> 01:03:36.097
HE HAD IN HIS OWN EARLY YEARS...

01:03:36.097 --> 01:03:39.134
AS A BOY, FOR EXAMPLE,
HE DEV WAYS

01:03:39.134 --> 01:03:43.038
-
AS A BOY, FOR EXAMPLE,
I THINK IT WAS CRANBERRIES--E-

01:03:43.038 --> 01:03:44.773
FROM UNRIPE CRANBERRIES.

01:03:44.773 --> 01:03:47.375
HE INVENTED A CANNON
THAT WOULD SHOOT THINGS

01:03:47.809 --> 01:03:49.544
OVER HIS NEIGHBOR'S FENCE.

01:03:49.544 --> 01:03:52.147
THIS WAS
THE KIND OF MAN HE WAS.

01:03:52.147 --> 01:03:55.617
HE WAS DEVELOPING NEW WAYS
TO DO EVERYDAY THINGS

01:03:55.617 --> 01:03:59.521
IN WAYS THAT WERE MORE
COMFORTABLE, MORE EFFICIENT.

01:03:59.521 --> 01:04:01.690
Osgood:
DURING WORLD WAR II

01:04:01.690 --> 01:04:04.726
SKINNER HAD DEVELOPED
A PIGEON GUIDANCE DEVICE

01:04:04.726 --> 01:04:06.895
FOR THE U.S. MILITARY.

01:04:06.895 --> 01:04:09.931
WHILE THE RUSSIANS
HAD DOGS CARRYING BOMBS

01:04:09.931 --> 01:04:13.401
AND THE SWEDES HAD SEALS
TO BLOW UP MINES

01:04:13.401 --> 01:04:15.570
SKINNER HAD A PLAN OF HIS OWN:

01:04:15.570 --> 01:04:20.341
TEACHING PIGEONS TO GUIDE
MISSILES TO AN ENEMY TARGET.

01:04:21.643 --> 01:04:23.378
AT THE TIME, HOWEVER

01:04:23.378 --> 01:04:25.113
THE AD
NO MISSILES TO GUIDE.

01:04:27.282 --> 01:04:30.752
BUT SKINNER'S PIGEON RESEARCH
DID NOT GO TO WASTE.

01:04:32.053 --> 01:04:35.523
HE DEVELOPS A SYSTEM
CALLED "OPERANT CONDITIONING"

01:04:35.523 --> 01:04:36.825
TO PROVE THAT A BEHAVIOR

01:04:36.825 --> 01:04:40.295
WILL BE REPEATED BY A SUBJECT
WHEN REWARDED.

01:04:40.295 --> 01:04:43.331
REPETITION LEADS
TO REINFORCEMENT...

01:04:43.331 --> 01:04:46.801
REINFORCEMENT
TO CHANGES IN BEHAVIOR.

01:04:46.801 --> 01:04:49.404
Announcer:
THIS HUNGRY PIGEON
IS MOVING ABOUT

01:04:49.404 --> 01:04:51.573
MORE OR LESS AT RANDOM.

01:04:51.573 --> 01:04:55.910
SOMETIMES IT TURNS ITS HEAD
TO THE LEFT.

01:04:55.910 --> 01:04:58.079
WHEN IT DOES, WE REINFORCE
THAT MOVEMENT

01:04:58.079 --> 01:05:01.116
BY GIVING THE PIGEON ACCESS
TO A DISH OF GRAIN.

01:05:03.718 --> 01:05:07.188
Osgood:
SKINNER THEN WAITS FOR IT
TO TURN FURTHER.

01:05:08.923 --> 01:05:10.225
AGAIN, MORE FOOD.

01:05:12.827 --> 01:05:15.864
ULTIMATELY THE PIGEON WILL TURN
IN A COMPLETE CIRCLE

01:05:15.864 --> 01:05:19.768
HAVING LEARNED THAT ONLY WHEN
HE TURNS WILL HE BE REWARDED.

01:05:24.105 --> 01:05:26.708
Singer:
WHAT SKINNER WAS ABLE TO DO

01:05:26.708 --> 01:05:30.612
IN VERY CAREFULLY CONTROLLED
STUDIES WITH ANIMAL MODELS

01:05:30.612 --> 01:05:34.082
WAS TO DEMONSTRATE
THAT WHOLE CHAINS OF BEHAVIORS

01:05:34.082 --> 01:05:36.251
COULD BE BUILT STEP-BY-STEP

01:05:36.251 --> 01:05:39.287
SO THAT LITERALLY YOU COULD
TEACH A PIGEON

01:05:39.287 --> 01:05:41.022
TO DO COMPLICATED BEHAVIORS

01:05:41.022 --> 01:05:43.625
THAT NO ONE WOULD
HAVE PREDICTED POSSIBLE.

01:05:47.095 --> 01:05:48.396
Osgood:
AND SKINNER BELIEVES

01:05:48.396 --> 01:05:50.999
THAT IF IT WORKS FOR PIGEONS,
WHY NOT PEOPLE?

01:05:52.734 --> 01:05:54.903
IN SKINNER'S MIND,
BEHAVIOR IS BEHAVIOR

01:05:55.336 --> 01:05:58.373
UP AND DOWN
THE EVOLUTIONARY SCALE

01:05:58.373 --> 01:05:59.674
AND IT IS ALL LEARNED.

01:06:03.578 --> 01:06:06.181
ONE OF THE GREAT SUCCESSES
IS IN EDUCATION.

01:06:06.181 --> 01:06:09.217
PEOPLE ARE TAUGHT
TO DO MORE COMPLICATED TASKS

01:06:09.217 --> 01:06:11.820
THAN ANYONE
HAD THOUGHT POSSIBLE

01:06:11.820 --> 01:06:18.326
BY BREAKING DOWN BEHAVIOR
INTO SMALL STEPS

01:06:23.531 --> 01:06:26.134
THE ESSENCE
OF SKINNER'S WORK WAS

01:06:26.134 --> 01:06:28.736
THAT WE COULD MANIPULATE
THE ENVIRONMENT

01:06:28.736 --> 01:06:31.339
IN WAYS THAT WOULD
PERMIT US TO PRODUCE

01:06:31.339 --> 01:06:33.942
ANY KIND OF BEHAVIOR
THAT WE WISHED

01:06:33.942 --> 01:06:36.544
AND WE COULD DEVELOP INDIVIDUALS
IN WAYS

01:06:36.544 --> 01:06:40.448
THAT MADE EVERY POSSIBLE FUTURE
OPEN TO THEM.

01:06:40.882 --> 01:06:43.918
Osgood:
THE IDEA THAT ANYTHING
IS POSSIBLE

01:06:43.918 --> 01:06:46.955
HAS ENORMOUS APPEAL
IN THE '50s--

01:06:46.955 --> 01:06:49.557
A TIME WHEN THE COUNTRY
IS CHANGING

01:06:49.557 --> 01:06:51.292
AT A MIND-BOGGLING PACE.

01:06:51.292 --> 01:06:53.420
IT'S THE BABY-BOOM ERA.

01:06:53.420 --> 01:06:56.497
MOTHERS WHO WORKED
DURING THE WAR

01:06:56.497 --> 01:06:59.100
ARE STAYING AT HOME
TO RAISE KIDS.

01:06:59.100 --> 01:07:02.136
WITH ECONOMIC GROWTH
AND UNPRECEDENTED MOBILITY

01:07:02.136 --> 01:07:04.739
YOUNG COUPLES ARE MOVING
AROUND THE COUNTRY

01:07:04.739 --> 01:07:08.643
LIVING FAR FROM THEIR PARENTS
AND EXTENDED FAMILIES.

01:07:08.643 --> 01:07:12.547
MOTHERS WANTING CHILD-REARING
ADVICE IN THIS BRAVE NEW WORLD

01:07:12.547 --> 01:07:18.620
MAY NOT BE ABLE TO TURN
TO THEIR OWN MOTHERS.

01:07:18.620 --> 01:07:20.788
AND HIS POPULAR BOOK.

01:07:20.788 --> 01:07:22.957
DR. BENJAMIN SPOCK
OFFERS ADVICE

01:07:22.957 --> 01:07:25.126
TO MILLIONS
OF WORRIED YOUNG PARENTS

01:07:25.126 --> 01:07:29.464
ABOUT HOW TO RAISE THEIR KIDS
IN THE PROPER ENVIRONMENT.

01:07:29.464 --> 01:07:32.500
HE COVERS EVERYTHING
FROM DIAPERS TO DISCIPLINE

01:07:32.934 --> 01:07:36.404
BORROWING IDEAS MORE FROM FREUD
THAN FROM SKINNER.

01:07:36.404 --> 01:07:39.874
HIS PARENTING MANUAL
SELLS MORE COPIES

01:07:39.874 --> 01:07:44.212
THAN ANY BOOK IN HISTORY
SAVE ONE-- THE BIBLE.

01:07:44.212 --> 01:07:47.248
Woman:
DR. SPOCK APPEALED TO THE NOTION

01:07:47.248 --> 01:07:50.285
THAT PARENTS AND EXPERTS

01:07:50.285 --> 01:07:53.755
WERE KIND OF IN THE
CHILD-NURTURE BUSINESS TOGETHER

01:07:53.755 --> 01:07:55.924
THAT THEY WERE COOPERATING

01:07:55.924 --> 01:08:01.562
TO PRODUCE HEALTHY CHILDREN,
DEMOCRATIC PERSONALITIES

01:08:01.562 --> 01:08:08.069
AND THAT CHILD-REARING MANUALS
LIKEBABY AND CHILD CARE

01:08:08.069 --> 01:08:14.575
COULD BE A USEFUL AID TO THOSE
KIND OF HOME-FRONT SCIENTISTS.

01:08:14.575 --> 01:08:18.913
Osgood:
HOME-FRONT SCIENTISTS
HUNGRY FOR EXPERT ADVICE.

01:08:19.347 --> 01:08:22.383
AND POPULAR TELEVISION
SATISFIES THEM

01:08:22.383 --> 01:08:25.420
BY BRINGING THE LATEST
IN LAB SCIENCE

01:08:25.420 --> 01:08:27.155
RIGHT INTO THEIR LIVING ROOMS.

01:08:27.155 --> 01:08:31.926
Announcer:
Conquest--the search
for new knowledge

01:08:31.926 --> 01:08:36.698
about our universe,
our world and ourselves.

01:08:38.866 --> 01:08:41.469
This monkey is an orphan

01:08:41.469 --> 01:08:44.505
separated from his mother
since the day of his birth.

01:08:44.505 --> 01:08:48.409
Literally his life
hangs by a thread--

01:08:48.409 --> 01:08:51.446
a soft cheesecloth pad

01:08:51.446 --> 01:08:54.916
that is his only companion,
his only comfort.

01:08:54.916 --> 01:08:58.386
Once a day, the pad
is removed for cleaning.

01:08:58.386 --> 01:09:01.856
Osgood:
THIS IS THE LABORATORY
OF PSYCHOLOGIST HARRY HARLOW.

01:09:01.856 --> 01:09:04.892
Announcer:
...is troubled, distressed.

01:09:04.892 --> 01:09:09.664
Osgood:
HE IS STUDYING MONKEYS TO BETTER
UNDERSTAND HUMAN RELATIONSHIPS.

01:09:09.664 --> 01:09:12.266
Announcer:
He may die for want of love.

01:09:12.266 --> 01:09:16.170
Osgood:
HARLOW BELIEVES HE CAN USE
SCIENCE TO STUDY LOVE.

01:09:17.905 --> 01:09:20.074
WITH A SERIES
OF PIONEERING EXPERIMENTS

01:09:20.074 --> 01:09:23.544
HE EXPLORES TERRITORY WHERE
FEW SCIENTISTS HAVE VENTURED.

01:09:23.544 --> 01:09:25.279
Herman:
HARLOW SAID

01:09:25.279 --> 01:09:30.051
THAT THERE WAS SUCH A THING AS
A SCIENCE OF LOVE, FOR EXAMPLE--

01:09:30.051 --> 01:09:32.220
THAT LOVE, THE KIND OF INTIMACY

01:09:32.220 --> 01:09:35.256
THAT CHARACTERIZED RELATIONSHIPS
BETWEEN MOTHERS AND INFANTS--

01:09:35.256 --> 01:09:40.461
ALTHOUGH IN HIS CASE
HE STUDIED MONKEYS--

01:09:40.461 --> 01:09:43.931
THAT YOU LITERALLY COULD
MOVE LOVE INTO A LABORATORY

01:09:43.931 --> 01:09:45.233
PUT IT UNDER A MICROSCOPE.

01:09:45.233 --> 01:09:48.703
Osgood:
HARLOW IS STUDYING LOVE

01:09:48.703 --> 01:09:51.305
BECAUSE HE BELIEVES IT MAKES
AN INDELIBLE IMPACT

01:09:51.305 --> 01:09:52.607
ON A YOUNG LIFE.

01:09:54.342 --> 01:09:57.378
THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN
A MOTHER AND HER CHILD--

01:09:57.378 --> 01:10:00.415
WHAT HARLOW CALLS OUR
EARLIEST SOCIAL ENVIRONMENT--

01:10:00.848 --> 01:10:04.318
COULD HOLD THE KEY TO EXPLAINING
BEHAVIOR THROUGHOUT LIFE.

01:10:04.318 --> 01:10:08.656
HARLOW DESIGNS A SET
OF INGENIOUS EXPERIMENTS:

01:10:08.656 --> 01:10:10.825
HE RAISES A BABY MONKEY

01:10:10.825 --> 01:10:17.331
ALLOWING IT TO CHOOSE
BETWEEN TWO SURROGATE MOTHERS:

01:10:17.331 --> 01:10:20.802
AND A CLOTH MOTHER
THAT DOESN'T--

01:10:20.802 --> 01:10:22.537
A CLOTH MOTHER
THAT HARLOW THINKS

01:10:22.537 --> 01:10:26.874
MIGHT PROVIDE SOMETHING ELSE:
COMFORT AND LOVE.

01:10:26.874 --> 01:10:31.646
Announcer:
Here's Baby 106

01:10:31.646 --> 01:10:34.682
weaned on a wire mother.

01:10:38.152 --> 01:10:41.189
He's going
to the wire mother.

01:10:42.490 --> 01:10:45.526
Osgood:
BUT THIS INFANT QUICKLY RUNS
TO THE CLOTH MOTHER

01:10:45.526 --> 01:10:48.996
WHERE HE WILL STAY FOR
THE NEXT 18 HOURS, CUDDLING...

01:10:55.937 --> 01:10:59.841
IN HARLOW'S MIND, CHOOSING
NURTURING OVER SUSTENANCE.

01:11:01.576 --> 01:11:05.480
IN ANOTHER EXPERIMENT, HARLOW
CREATES A FEARFUL SITUATION.

01:11:05.480 --> 01:11:07.648
WHOM DOES THE INFANT
TURN TO NOW?

01:11:07.648 --> 01:11:12.420
Announcer:
Let's find out what his
reactions to his mother are

01:11:12.420 --> 01:11:15.022
when we frighten him.

01:11:18.059 --> 01:11:20.588
He's scared, all right

01:11:20.588 --> 01:11:24.565
and he does what any child
will do in a similar situation:

01:11:24.565 --> 01:11:27.602
he was runningtohis mother
to touch her

01:11:27.602 --> 01:11:29.770
to drive away his fear.

01:11:29.770 --> 01:11:35.843
(screeching)

01:11:35.843 --> 01:11:39.747
Osgood:
TO HARLOW, THERE IS SOMETHING
ABOUT THE EXPERIENCE OF COMFORT

01:11:39.747 --> 01:11:42.350
AND LOVE-- EVEN MORE THAN FOOD--

01:11:42.350 --> 01:11:44.952
THAT SEEMS CRUCIAL
TO ALL THESE MONKEYS.

01:11:46.687 --> 01:11:50.158
BUT WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN THE INFANT IS RAISED ALONE

01:11:50.158 --> 01:11:52.760
WITHOUT ANY MOTHER AT ALL,
WIRE OR CLOTH?

01:11:55.363 --> 01:11:57.965
IN THIS SITUATION,
THE ORPHAN MONKEY STAYS ALONE.

01:11:57.965 --> 01:12:01.002
HE WON'T EVEN GO TO
THE CLOTH MOTHER WHEN FRIGHTENED

01:12:01.002 --> 01:12:04.038
BUT RETREATS INTO HIS OWN WORLD.

01:12:04.472 --> 01:12:07.508
HARLOW BELIEVES HE HAS SHOWN
HOW WANT OF LOVE

01:12:07.508 --> 01:12:09.677
CAN DAMAGE AN INFANT FOR LIFE

01:12:09.677 --> 01:12:14.015
AND HE WORRIES THE SAME IS TRUE
FOR PEOPLE.

01:12:17.051 --> 01:12:18.352
IN HARRY HARLOW'S EXPERIMENT

01:12:18.352 --> 01:12:22.256
WAS THAT EARLY EXPERIENCE
AND THE ENVIRONMENT WERE CRUCIAL

01:12:22.256 --> 01:12:25.293
TO THE HEALTHY DEVELOPMENT
OF THE INFANT CHILD

01:12:25.293 --> 01:12:27.461
AND THAT IN A SENSE,
IF YOU MESSED UP

01:12:27.461 --> 01:12:30.064
IF THE RIGHT KIND OF
MATERNAL PRESENCE WAS NOT THERE

01:12:30.498 --> 01:12:33.534
DURING THE CRITICAL YEARS,
THEN THAT INFANT MIGHT GROW UP

01:12:33.534 --> 01:12:37.004
TO BE AN ADULT INCAPABLE OF
FORMING HEALTHY RELATIONSHIPS

01:12:37.004 --> 01:12:38.739
WITH OTHER KINDS OF PEOPLE.

01:12:40.474 --> 01:12:43.945
Osgood:
WHILE HARLOW FEELS THAT
A BAD ENVIRONMENT CAN DAMAGE YOU

01:12:43.945 --> 01:12:45.680
THERE ARE OTHERS WHO BELIEVE

01:12:45.680 --> 01:12:50.451
THAT A THERAPEUTIC ENVIRONMENT
COULD PROVIDE THE CURE.

01:12:50.451 --> 01:12:53.921
CHIEF AMONG THEM
