TRAINED FIRST IN GERMANY
AS A NEUROLOGIST

01:14:15.903 --> 01:14:19.373
SHE BELIEVES DEEPLY
THAT INSIDE EVERY PATIENT

01:14:19.373 --> 01:14:21.542
NO MATTER
HOW SERIOUSLY DISTURBED

01:14:25.880 --> 01:14:28.049
IF THE TREATMENT IS RIGHT.

01:14:28.049 --> 01:14:31.519
Hornstein:
SHE DEVELOPED THIS ATTITUDE
PARTLY HAVING WORKED

01:14:31.519 --> 01:14:34.555
WITH BRAIN-INJURED PATIENTS
IN WORLD WAR I

01:14:34.555 --> 01:14:36.724
WHERE EVEN THOSE PATIENTS

01:14:36.724 --> 01:14:39.327
WHO HAD BEEN HIT
BY SHELLS AND GASSED

01:14:39.327 --> 01:14:43.230
WERE PEOPLE WHO COULD RECOVER
TO A CERTAIN EXTENT.

01:14:43.230 --> 01:14:45.399
AND HER WHOLE APPROACH TO THEM

01:14:45.399 --> 01:14:48.436
WAS BASED ON THEIR POTENTIAL
FOR RECOVERY

01:14:48.436 --> 01:14:53.207
NOT FOR WHAT WAS DAMAGED.

01:14:53.207 --> 01:14:55.376
SHE APPLIED
THIS SAME ORIENTATION

01:14:55.810 --> 01:14:58.412
AND ALWAYS SEARCHED
FOR THE PART OF THE PATIENT

01:14:58.412 --> 01:15:00.581
THAT WAS STILL INTACT.

01:15:01.882 --> 01:15:05.228
Osgood:
WHEN FROMM-REICHMANN EMIGRATES
TO THE UNITED STATES

01:15:09.690 --> 01:15:11.859
BUILT AS A RESORT IN THE 1890s

01:15:11.859 --> 01:15:14.462
ON THE OUTSKIRTS
OF WASHINGTON, D.C.

01:15:14.462 --> 01:15:17.498
IT IS LATER CONVERTED
INTO A MENTAL HOSPITAL.

