01:15:49.597 --> 01:15:53.836
Man:
CHESTNUT LODGE
WAS A STRANGE PLACE

01:15:53.836 --> 01:15:56.537
ALMOST A MYTHICAL ONE

01:15:56.537 --> 01:15:58.706
BECAUSE WE HAD
FAIRLY GOOD EVIDENCE

01:15:58.706 --> 01:16:00.875
THAT THEY REALLY COULD MAKE

01:16:00.875 --> 01:16:03.911
A THERAPEUTIC IMPACT
THAT WAS SIGNIFICANT

01:16:03.911 --> 01:16:08.249
ON SCHIZOPHRENIC PATIENTS
SIMPLY BY PSYCHOTHERAPY ALONE.

01:16:10.418 --> 01:16:12.153
Osgood:
SCHIZOPHRENIA--

01:16:12.153 --> 01:16:15.623
AN ILLNESS MARKED BY A LOSS
OF CONTACT WITH REALITY

01:16:15.623 --> 01:16:20.828
BY HALLUCINATIONS, VOICES,
PARANOIA.

01:16:20.828 --> 01:16:23.431
IT IS NOT WELL UNDERSTOOD
IN THE 1950s

01:16:23.431 --> 01:16:28.556
WHEN A YOUNG GIRL FROM BROOKLYN
ARRIVES, SEEKING HELP.

01:16:28.556 --> 01:16:33.841
JOANNE GREENBERG WAITED
THREE YEARS

01:16:33.841 --> 01:16:37.745
SHE FINALLY ENTERS TWO DAYS
AFTER HER 16th BIRTHDAY.

01:16:39.914 --> 01:16:43.384
SHE WOULD LATER WRITE
ABOUT HER ILLNESS AND TREATMENT

01:16:43.384 --> 01:16:47.721
IN A BEST-SELLING BOOK,I NEVER
PROMISED YOU A ROSE GARDEN.

01:16:49.890 --> 01:16:53.794
Greenberg:
I HAD NO IDEA OF WHAT
WAS GOING ON ON THE OUTSIDE

01:16:53.794 --> 01:16:56.397
BUT I WAS TRYING
WITH EVERYTHING I HAD

01:16:56.397 --> 01:17:00.734
AND I HAD BEEN
SINCE THE AGE OF SIX

01:17:00.734 --> 01:17:04.638
TO TRY AND MAKE IT RIGHT,
TO TRY AND FIX IT.

01:17:08.108 --> 01:17:11.579
I THINK THE WORST FEAR SOMEHOW
IS NOT TO BE ALL RIGHT

01:17:11.579 --> 01:17:13.747
AND IT'S ONLY LATER
WHEN YOU FINALLY SAY

01:17:13.747 --> 01:17:16.350
A) YOU ARE NEVER
GOING TO BE ALL RIGHT

01:17:16.350 --> 01:17:19.386
IT IS NEVER GOING TO BE
ALL RIGHT

01:17:19.820 --> 01:17:23.724
THAT YOU SAY, "WELL, OKAY,
LET IT, LET IT ALL GO."

01:17:25.459 --> 01:17:28.929
"TELL THEM ABOUT THE BLOOD
COMING OUT OF THE FAUCETS."

01:17:30.231 --> 01:17:35.002
I'D SEE PEOPLE WALKING ALONG
WHO WERE JUST MASSES OF MAGGOTS.

01:17:35.002 --> 01:17:38.906
ALL RIGHT, YOU KNOW,
TELL THEM ABOUT IT.

01:17:38.906 --> 01:17:40.641
WELL, I DID.

01:17:44.979 --> 01:17:48.015
Osgood:
FROMM-REICHMANN MEETS
WITH JOANNE DAILY.

01:17:48.015 --> 01:17:53.654
SHE TREATS HER WITH A VARIATION
OF THE SO-CALLED "TALKING CURE."

01:17:53.654 --> 01:17:56.257
SITTING WITH HER PATIENTS--
LISTENING, TALKING--

01:17:56.690 --> 01:17:58.859
EVEN WHILE THEY WERE
HALLUCINATING

01:17:58.859 --> 01:18:01.896
WITHDRAWN, RECALCITRANT.

01:18:04.498 --> 01:18:08.836
Man:
IT WAS A VERY SIMPLE IDEA--
TALK TO PATIENTS.

01:18:08.836 --> 01:18:10.571
LET THEM TALK TO YOU.

01:18:10.571 --> 01:18:14.475
TAKE THEM SERIOUSLY,
TREAT THEM AS HUMAN BEINGS.

01:18:14.909 --> 01:18:20.548
PEOPLE WERE NOT JUST STRUGGLING
WITH PSYCHOSIS, WITH INSANITY.

01:18:20.548 --> 01:18:25.753
THEY ALSO HAD NONPSYCHOTIC
ASPECTS TO THEIR MINDS

01:18:25.753 --> 01:18:27.054
TO THEIR PERSON

01:18:27.054 --> 01:18:31.392
AND THAT IF YOU COULD
HOLD ONTO THAT ASPECT

01:18:31.392 --> 01:18:33.561
YOU COULD MAKE A DIFFERENCE.

01:18:37.464 --> 01:18:40.935
Greenberg:
I HAD THERAPY
FOUR TIMES A WEEK.

01:18:40.935 --> 01:18:43.971
BUT FOR THOSE YEARS
THAT I WAS IN THE HOSPITAL

01:18:43.971 --> 01:18:46.574
THAT'S ALL I DID,
AND THAT TOOK EVERYTHING I HAD.

01:18:47.007 --> 01:18:51.345
IT'S A VERY, VERY
DIFFICULT PROCESS.

01:18:53.514 --> 01:18:55.683
MY ALLY HAD A FIRST-RATE MIND

01:18:55.683 --> 01:18:59.587
AND WOULD NOT ALLOW ME
TO GET AWAY WITH MUCH.

01:18:59.587 --> 01:19:08.696
SHE WAS TRYING TO ELICIT FROM ME
THINGS ABOUT MY LIFE

01:19:08.696 --> 01:19:16.070
THAT COUNTED IN THE WAY
I SAW REALITY.

01:19:16.070 --> 01:19:19.974
IT DOESN'T SOUND LIKE MUCH--
YOU TELL THE DOCTOR THINGS

01:19:19.974 --> 01:19:24.311
AND THE DOCTOR HEARS
AND LISTENS

01:19:24.311 --> 01:19:27.781
BUT I THINK IT REROUTES
YOUR BRAIN.

01:19:27.781 --> 01:19:31.251
I THINK IT REROUTES
YOUR SENSE OF REALITY.

01:19:31.251 --> 01:19:37.758
I THINK IT REWIRES YOU...
(laughs) SOMEHOW

01:19:37.758 --> 01:19:43.397
UH... BECAUSE
WHEN THAT CHANGE HAPPENS...

01:19:46.433 --> 01:19:49.470
IT'S A PROFOUND CHANGE.

01:19:52.506 --> 01:19:55.109
Osgood:
JOANNE GREENBERG
LEAVES CHESTNUT LODGE

01:19:55.109 --> 01:19:56.844
THREE YEARS AFTER SHE ARRIVED.

01:19:56.844 --> 01:20:00.748
TWICE SHE RETURNS
FOR SHORT STAYS.

01:20:01.181 --> 01:20:02.483
BUT ULTIMATELY

01:20:02.483 --> 01:20:09.423
JOANNE GOES TO COLLEGE, MARRIES,
RAISES HER CHILDREN AND WRITES.

01:20:09.423 --> 01:20:10.724
FOR JOANNE GREENBERG

01:20:10.724 --> 01:20:14.194
FROMM-REICHMANN'S TALKING CURE
WAS ENOUGH.

01:20:15.929 --> 01:20:18.532
BUT THIS TURNS OUT
TO BE UNUSUAL.

01:20:18.532 --> 01:20:22.436
MOST PSYCHOTICS TREATED SOLELY
BY TALKING THERAPY

01:20:22.436 --> 01:20:24.171
EVENTUALLY RELAPSE.

01:20:24.171 --> 01:20:26.340
SO, EVEN UNDER
THE BEST OF CIRCUMSTANCES

01:20:26.340 --> 01:20:28.075
WITH THE MOST COMMITTED
CLINICIANS

01:20:28.075 --> 01:20:31.979
HO BELIEVE
WITH THE MOST COMMITTED
THE ENVIRONMENT CAN CURERS W

01:20:31.979 --> 01:20:35.015
ONLY ACHIEVE OCCASIONAL SUCCESS.

01:20:38.485 --> 01:20:41.088
AND IN THE UNITED STATES
IN THE 1950s

01:20:41.088 --> 01:20:43.691
MOST OF THE SEVERELY
MENTALLY ILL

01:20:43.691 --> 01:20:48.028
ARE NOT IN THE BEST HOSPITALS
UNDER THE BEST CIRCUMSTANCES.

01:20:48.028 --> 01:20:51.932
THEY END UP IN STATE
MENTAL INSTITUTIONS.

01:20:51.932 --> 01:20:55.402
HERE THERE IS A DIFFERENT
THEORETICAL ORIENTATION

01:20:55.402 --> 01:21:01.041
ONE ROOTED IN BIOLOGY,
BUT AGAIN WITH LITTLE SUCCESS.

01:21:01.041 --> 01:21:04.511
McGlashan:
THEY BELIEVED THAT
SEVERE MENTAL ILLNESS

01:21:04.511 --> 01:21:07.981
WERE BASICALLY ORGANIC
NEUROLOGICAL DISORDERS;

01:21:07.981 --> 01:21:12.319
ESSENTIALLY IRREVERSIBLE,
LIKE MOST NEUROLOGIC DISORDERS

01:21:12.319 --> 01:21:16.223
AND THAT THE VICTIMS,
THE PATIENTS

01:21:16.657 --> 01:21:19.693
TO BE TAKEN CARE OF

01:21:19.693 --> 01:21:24.031
AND OFTEN TAKEN CARE OF
FOR THE REST OF THEIR LIVES.

