THIS IS COMMON PRACTICE

01:26:28.535 --> 01:26:31.571
IN THIS PRE-SPUTNIK ERA
OF SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH.

01:26:31.571 --> 01:26:35.475
AFTER THAT,
HIS PSYCHOTIC PATIENTS.

01:26:35.475 --> 01:26:37.210
Lehmann:
AFTER TWO WEEKS

01:26:37.210 --> 01:26:39.813
TWO OF THE PATIENTS
WENT INTO REMISSION--

01:26:39.813 --> 01:26:41.982
WERE COMPLETELY FREE
OF SYMPTOMS.

01:26:41.982 --> 01:26:43.717
NOW, THAT I'D NEVER SEEN.

01:26:43.717 --> 01:26:45.886
IT ISN'T
IN THE TEXTBOOKS EITHER

01:26:46.319 --> 01:26:48.922
AND IT WAS WHAT
THE FRENCH HAD DESCRIBED.

01:26:48.922 --> 01:26:50.657
UM... I DIDN'T BELIEVE IT.

01:26:50.657 --> 01:26:52.392
I THOUGHT IT WAS A FLUKE.

01:26:54.127 --> 01:26:56.296
BUT THEN, AFTER
THREE OR FOUR WEEKS

01:26:56.296 --> 01:27:00.200
QUITE A FEW MORE PATIENTS
WERE SYMPTOM-FREE.

01:27:00.200 --> 01:27:04.971
WE HAD SOMETHING THAT WOULD
TURN IT OFF LIKE A WATER TAP.

01:27:04.971 --> 01:27:07.140
SYMPTOMS WOULD DISAPPEAR

01:27:07.140 --> 01:27:09.309
WHETHER YOU
UNDERSTOOD THEM OR NOT

01:27:09.309 --> 01:27:11.912
NO MATTER WHAT THE DYNAMICS
MIGHT HAVE BEEN.

01:27:16.249 --> 01:27:18.418
IT WAS LIKE TAKING AN ASPIRIN
FOR A TOOTHACHE--

01:27:18.852 --> 01:27:21.021
IT JUST CUT IT OFF.

01:27:21.021 --> 01:27:23.623
IT DIDN'T CURE THE TOOTHACHE
OR THE BAD TOOTH

01:27:23.623 --> 01:27:25.792
BUT THE SYMPTOMS
DISAPPEARED COMPLETELY.

01:27:25.792 --> 01:27:31.431
Osgood:
IT IS A NEW KIND OF TREATMENT:
A MEDICATION FOR THE MIND.

01:27:31.431 --> 01:27:34.034
BEFORE, THEY HAD
ONLY BARBITURATES

01:27:34.034 --> 01:27:36.636
WHICH WOULD KNOCK PATIENTS OUT.

01:27:36.636 --> 01:27:40.107
NOW THEY HAVE A DRUG
THAT REDUCES PSYCHOSIS

01:27:40.107 --> 01:27:43.577
WITHOUT REDUCING THE LEVEL
OF CONSCIOUSNESS.

01:27:43.577 --> 01:27:45.745
IT IS A WHOLE NEW KIND
OF PHARMACY--

01:27:45.745 --> 01:27:49.216
ONE THAT SEEMS TO TARGET
JUST THE DISEASE.

01:27:51.818 --> 01:27:53.553
IN A SENSE, THE DRUG
TREATMENT OF SCHIZOPHRENIA

01:27:53.553 --> 01:27:56.156
HAPPENED LIKE ALL OF THE
TREATMENTS OF SCHIZOPHRENIA--

01:27:56.590 --> 01:28:00.494
THAT YOU ARE WORKING
FROM DESPERATION

01:28:00.494 --> 01:28:05.265
AND IF SOMETHING LOOKS
LIKE IT MIGHT MAKE AN EFFECT

01:28:05.265 --> 01:28:07.000
YOU TRY IT

01:28:07.000 --> 01:28:09.169
BECAUSE YOU HAVEN'T GOT
ANYTHING TO LOSE.

01:28:09.169 --> 01:28:14.374
AND SO THEY TRIED IT,
AND THIS TIME IT... IT WORKED.

01:28:16.543 --> 01:28:20.881
Osgood:
AND CHLORPROMAZINE
IS JUST THE BEGINNING.

01:28:20.881 --> 01:28:23.917
FROM PILLS FOR THE SEVERELY
MENTALLY ILL

01:28:23.917 --> 01:28:26.953
TO TRANQUILIZERS
FOR THE MILDLY ANXIOUS.

01:28:29.990 --> 01:28:32.940
FROM LITHIUM AND RESERPINE
IN THE 1950s

01:28:32.940 --> 01:28:36.062
TO MILTOWN AND VALIUM
BY THE 1960s.

01:28:37.364 --> 01:28:42.135
MEDICATIONS FOR THE MIND BECOME
A NEW PART OF AMERICAN LIFE.

01:28:43.870 --> 01:28:47.774
HOW ANY OF THESE DRUGS WORK,
NO ONE KNOWS AT FIRST.

01:28:47.774 --> 01:28:49.075
BUT THERE'S NO DOUBT

01:28:49.509 --> 01:28:53.847
THAT SOMEHOW THE DRUGS CHANGE
BEHAVIOR BY ALTERING THE BRAIN.

01:28:53.847 --> 01:28:56.883
THE BRAIN IS THE KEY.

01:28:56.883 --> 01:28:58.185
THE PSYCHOTROPIC DRUGS

01:28:58.185 --> 01:29:00.353
HAD EFFECTIVELY BEEN
DISCOVERED EMPIRICALLY.

01:29:00.353 --> 01:29:03.823
NO ONE KNEW WHY THEY WORKED,
BUT THEY DID WORK.

01:29:03.823 --> 01:29:06.426
SO THE NEXT QUESTION WAS:
WHY DID THEY WORK?

01:29:07.727 --> 01:29:09.896
Osgood:
IN LABORATORIES
ALL OVER THE WORLD

01:29:09.896 --> 01:29:11.631
FROM SWEDEN TO THE UNITED STATES

01:29:11.631 --> 01:29:16.403
SCIENTISTS ARE TRYING
TO ANSWER THIS QUESTION.

01:29:16.403 --> 01:29:19.439
SOLOMON SNYDER IS ONE OF THEM.

01:29:19.873 --> 01:29:23.343
IN 1975,
SNYDER AND HIS COLLEAGUES EMBARK

01:29:23.343 --> 01:29:25.512
ON A SERIES
OF ANIMAL EXPERIMENTS

01:29:25.512 --> 01:29:29.416
AT JOHNS HOPKINS UNIVERSITY
TO SEE HOW CHLORPROMAZINE WORKS.

01:29:36.790 --> 01:29:40.694
HE INJECTS RATS WITH THE DRUG
TO SEE HOW IT AFFECTS THE BRAIN.

01:29:45.465 --> 01:29:48.935
WHAT HE DISCOVERS IS
A CHANGE IN BRAIN CHEMISTRY.

01:29:53.273 --> 01:29:56.743
CHLORPROMAZINE SEEMS TO AFFECT
ONE CHEMICAL IN PARTICULAR

01:29:56.743 --> 01:29:58.478
CALLED DOPAMINE.

01:30:04.117 --> 01:30:06.720
THE BRAIN--
OF A RAT OR A HUMAN--

01:30:06.720 --> 01:30:09.322
IS MADE UP OF THESE
KINDS OF CHEMICALS

01:30:09.322 --> 01:30:11.057
CALLED NEUROTRANSMITTERS.

01:30:13.660 --> 01:30:15.395
NEUROTRANSMITTERS
ALLOW BRAIN CELLS

01:30:15.395 --> 01:30:19.299
TO COMMUNICATE WITH EACH OTHER,
MAKING UP AN INTRICATE NETWORK.

01:30:22.769 --> 01:30:25.372
ULTIMATELY,
WHAT SNYDER'S EXPERIMENTS

01:30:25.372 --> 01:30:27.107
AND OTHERS LIKE HIS SHOW

01:30:27.107 --> 01:30:29.276
IS THAT THERE IS
AN INTIMATE CONNECTION

01:30:29.276 --> 01:30:32.312
BETWEEN NEUROTRANSMITTERS
AND BEHAVIOR.

01:30:34.047 --> 01:30:37.083
BETDOPAMINE IS LINKEDTERS
WITH SCHIZOPHRENIA.

01:30:40.940 --> 01:30:44.024
OTHER EXPERIMENTS LINK
THE NEUROTRANSMITTER SEROTONIN

01:30:44.024 --> 01:30:45.325
WITH DEPRESSION...

01:30:47.060 --> 01:30:49.663
ACETYLCHOLINE WITH MEMORY.

01:30:51.398 --> 01:30:53.566
IN FACT, THESE NEUROTRANSMITTERS

01:30:54.000 --> 01:30:57.470
AND THE CHEMICAL REACTIONS
THEY PRODUCE IN THE BRAIN

01:30:57.470 --> 01:31:00.940
ARE WHAT CAUSE BEHAVIOR,
NORMAL AND ABNORMAL.

01:31:02.242 --> 01:31:06.579
THE REALIZATION
THAT THE BRAIN WORKS

01:31:06.579 --> 01:31:10.483
ON THE BASIS OF CHEMICAL SIGNALS

01:31:10.483 --> 01:31:12.218
WHICH ARE DYNAMIC

01:31:12.218 --> 01:31:16.122
AND WHICH ARE
CHANGING ALL THE TIME

01:31:16.122 --> 01:31:20.460
REPRESENTED A MAJOR REVOLUTION
IN BIOLOGY

01:31:20.460 --> 01:31:22.195
REPRESENTED A MAJOR REVOLUTION
IN BIOLOGYS ANALOGOUS

01:31:22.195 --> 01:31:27.400
TO THE REVOLUTION THAT GALILEO
USHERED IN CENTURIES AGO.

01:31:27.400 --> 01:31:31.738
NO LONGER COULD
WE REGARD THE BRAIN

01:31:31.738 --> 01:31:37.811
AS AN UNCHANGING,
IMMUTABLE SWITCHBOARD

01:31:37.811 --> 01:31:41.715
WITH WHICH WE WERE
BLESSED OR CURSED FOREVER.

01:31:41.715 --> 01:31:47.787
THE CHEMICAL HYPOTHESIS OF BRAIN
FUNCTION AND BRAIN MESSAGES

01:31:47.787 --> 01:31:51.691
MEANT THAT WE COULD
UNDERSTAND BEHAVIOR

01:31:51.691 --> 01:31:56.029
AND THAT WE MIGHT
BE ABLE TO CHANGE BEHAVIOR.

01:31:56.029 --> 01:32:00.800
THE DISCOVERY THAT
WE ARE PEOPLE WITH BRAINS

01:32:00.800 --> 01:32:04.704
AND THAT BRAINS ARE REGULATED
BY VARIOUS BIOLOGICAL PROCESSES

01:32:04.704 --> 01:32:09.042
HAS CERTAINLY SHAKEN
THE OLDER VIEW

01:32:09.042 --> 01:32:12.078
THAT WE REALLY
ARE SPIRITUAL BEINGS

01:32:12.078 --> 01:32:14.247
AND THAT BRAINS BE DAMNED.

01:32:14.247 --> 01:32:15.982
THEY'RE JUST KIND
OF THE HARDWARE--

01:32:15.982 --> 01:32:18.151
LIKE OUR MUSCLES
AND OUR HEART, ETC.--

01:32:18.151 --> 01:32:20.754
THAT WE NEED
TO BE SPIRITUAL BEINGS.

01:32:20.754 --> 01:32:24.224
THE FACT THAT WE KNOW
THAT WE HAVE BRAINS

01:32:24.224 --> 01:32:28.128
AND THAT WE CAN RADICALLY
INFLUENCE THE WAY WE THINK

01:32:28.128 --> 01:32:30.730
BY INGESTION
OF CERTAIN CHEMICALS--

01:32:30.730 --> 01:32:34.634
CERTAIN PURE CHEMICALS
THAT WE KNOW THE IDENTITY OF--

01:32:34.634 --> 01:32:38.104
HAS REALLY CHANGED
OUR CONCEPTION OF OURSELVES

01:32:38.104 --> 01:32:40.273
AND THERE'S NO GOING BACK.

01:32:42.876 --> 01:32:47.647
MUCH AS SOME MIGHT WISH IT,
THERE IS NO GOING BACK AT ALL.

01:32:47.647 --> 01:32:49.816
THE CHEMICAL REVOLUTION
OF THE 1970s

01:32:49.816 --> 01:32:52.852
BEGETS A WHOLE NEW
BIOLOGY OF BEHAVIOR--

01:32:52.852 --> 01:32:57.190
A BIOLOGY OF THOUGHT,
A BIOLOGY OF EMOTION.

01:32:57.624 --> 01:32:59.793
SOME SCIENTISTS
BEGIN TO ASK THIS:

01:32:59.793 --> 01:33:05.432
IF THE BRAIN CAN BE PHYSICALLY
CHANGED BY PILLS LIKE THESE

01:33:05.432 --> 01:33:09.769
CAN IT ALSO BE CHANGED
JUST BY EXPERIENCE?

01:33:09.769 --> 01:33:11.070
ONE ANSWER COMES

01:33:11.070 --> 01:33:15.408
FROM THIS UNASSUMING
CREATURE, A SEA SLUG.

01:33:15.408 --> 01:33:18.011
ITS ANATOMY IS
A WORLD APART FROM OURS

01:33:18.011 --> 01:33:20.613
BUT ITS BIOCHEMISTRY
IS SIMILAR ENOUGH

01:33:20.613 --> 01:33:22.348
TO RUN A CRUCIAL EXPERIMENT.

01:33:22.348 --> 01:33:24.083
BEGINNING IN THE 1970s

01:33:24.083 --> 01:33:27.120
WORK WITH SLUGS DEMONSTRATES
THAT IT IS POSSIBLE

01:33:27.120 --> 01:33:29.722
TO PHYSICALLY CHANGE
THE BRAIN'S BIOCHEMISTRY

01:33:29.722 --> 01:33:31.458
JUST THROUGH LEARNING;

01:33:31.458 --> 01:33:34.494
THAT THE BRAIN DOES, IN FACT,
RESPOND TO EXPERIENCE

01:33:34.494 --> 01:33:37.530
AND IS ACTUALLY CHANGED BY IT.

01:33:37.530 --> 01:33:41.868
OF COURSE, A SLUG IS...
WELL, JUST A SLUG, NOT A PERSON

01:33:41.868 --> 01:33:43.169
BUT IT DOES PROVE

01:33:43.169 --> 01:33:46.206
THAT EXPERIENCE CAN NEVER
AGAIN BE SO EASILY DIVORCED

01:33:46.206 --> 01:33:47.941
FROM BIOLOGY.

01:33:47.941 --> 01:33:50.543
IT'S THE BEGINNING
OF A NEW, REVOLUTIONARY WAY

01:33:50.543 --> 01:33:52.278
OF THINKING ABOUT BEHAVIOR--

01:33:52.278 --> 01:33:55.748
A NEW SYNTHESIS, PUTTING
TO REST THE OLD DICHOTOMY

01:33:55.748 --> 01:33:58.351
BETWEEN NATURE AND NURTURE--

01:33:58.351 --> 01:34:01.821
A SYNTHESIS THAT WOULD
EVEN INCLUDE GENETICS.

01:34:04.858 --> 01:34:07.460
(choir singing
Handel's "Messiah")

01:34:07.460 --> 01:34:10.063
Osgood:
SALT LAKE CITY, UTAH.

01:34:10.063 --> 01:34:11.798
HOME TO THE MORMON CHURCH

01:34:11.798 --> 01:34:15.702
WHICH HAS ATTRACTED SETTLERS
FOR OVER A HUNDRED YEARS.

01:34:20.473 --> 01:34:21.774
A TIGHT-KNIT COMMUNITY

01:34:21.774 --> 01:34:25.678
THE MORMONS PROVIDE A NATURAL
LABORATORY FOR GENETICISTS

01:34:25.678 --> 01:34:27.413
LOOKING TO SEE
HOW TRAITS ARE PASSED

01:34:27.413 --> 01:34:30.016
FROM GENERATION TO GENERATION.

01:34:32.619 --> 01:34:36.956
IN THE 1970s, THE CHURCH DECIDED
TO OPEN ITS DOORS TO SCIENTISTS

01:34:36.956 --> 01:34:41.294
SHARING ITS VAST
GENEALOGICAL RECORDS.

01:34:41.294 --> 01:34:43.463
MORMON LEADERS DID TWO THINGS

01:34:43.463 --> 01:34:46.499
FOR WHICH GENETICISTS
WILL FOREVER BE THANKFUL.

01:34:46.499 --> 01:34:50.403
NCOURAGED THEIR FOLLOWERS
FOR WHICH GENETICISTS
TO BE FRUITFUL AND MULTIPLYY E

01:34:50.403 --> 01:34:52.138
AND, AS PART OF CHURCH PRACTICE

01:34:52.138 --> 01:34:54.741
THEY URGED THEM TO KEEP
FASTIDIOUS RECORDS

01:34:54.741 --> 01:34:56.910
OF THEIR FAMILY HISTORIES.

01:34:56.910 --> 01:35:00.813
SOME GO BACK
AS FAR AS 150 YEARS.

01:35:02.115 --> 01:35:04.284
THIS IS HOW HUMAN GENETICS
HAS BEEN STUDIED

01:35:04.284 --> 01:35:06.019
THROUGHOUT THE CENTURY--

01:35:06.019 --> 01:35:08.621
MAKING INFERENCES ABOUT
PATTERNS OF INHERITANCE

01:35:09.055 --> 01:35:11.658
BY STUDYING THE ANCESTRY
OF LARGE FAMILIES.

01:35:11.658 --> 01:35:14.260
THIS IS HOW THE INHERITANCE
OF DISEASES

01:35:14.260 --> 01:35:17.297
LIKE A FATAL BLOOD DISORDER
FOUND AMONG MORMONS

01:35:17.730 --> 01:35:19.032
IS TRACKED.

01:35:19.032 --> 01:35:20.767
OR THE INHERITANCE
OF BEHAVIORAL DISORDERS

01:35:20.767 --> 01:35:26.406
LIKE MANIC DEPRESSION, SEEN
AMONG THE AMISH IN PENNSYLVANIA.

01:35:26.406 --> 01:35:29.876
ALL THIS WOULD CHANGE
BY THE 1980s.

01:35:30.310 --> 01:35:33.780
SCIENTISTS NO LONGER HAVE TO
RELY SOLELY ON FAMILY RECORDS

01:35:33.780 --> 01:35:35.515
TO UNDERSTAND GENETICS.

01:35:35.515 --> 01:35:38.985
THEY HAVE DISCOVERED WAYS TO
WORK WITH THE GENES THEMSELVES.

01:35:38.985 --> 01:35:43.323
THEY CAN WORK WITH DNA-- THE
MATERIAL THAT MAKES UP GENES

01:35:43.323 --> 01:35:47.226
THAT CARRIES THE BLUEPRINT
FOR HOW EACH OF US DEVELOPS

01:35:47.226 --> 01:35:49.829
THAT PROVIDES
THE GENETIC INSTRUCTIONS

01:35:50.263 --> 01:35:52.432
DIRECTING OUR BRAIN CHEMISTRY.

01:35:52.432 --> 01:35:55.902
SCIENTISTS,
LIKE WALTER GILBERT AT HARVARD

01:35:55.902 --> 01:35:58.504
AND DAVID BOTSTEIN AT M.I.T.

01:35:58.504 --> 01:36:00.239
DEVELOPED METHODS TO DECIPHER

01:36:00.239 --> 01:36:03.710
THE 100,000 GENES
IN EACH ONE OF US.

01:36:03.710 --> 01:36:07.614
THIS ENABLES GENETICISTS
TO DETECT PATTERNS--

01:36:07.614 --> 01:36:11.517
THE DNA SEQUENCES THAT
MAKE INDIVIDUALS DIFFERENT.

01:36:11.517 --> 01:36:16.723
SCIENTISTS CAN NOW PICK OUT
AN ANOMALOUS GENE, A MUTATION.

01:36:16.723 --> 01:36:19.759
THEY CAN SEARCH FOR GENES
THAT CAUSE DISEASES

01:36:19.759 --> 01:36:22.795
LIKE CYSTIC FIBROSIS;

01:36:22.795 --> 01:36:25.398
OR ONES THAT CONTRIBUTE
TO BEHAVIORAL DISORDERS

01:36:25.398 --> 01:36:28.434
LIKE DEPRESSION
OR ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE.

01:36:30.603 --> 01:36:32.338
Man:
HAVING THE TECHNOLOGY

01:36:32.338 --> 01:36:35.375
LED TO A VERY HIGH LEVEL
OF EXCITEMENT

01:36:35.375 --> 01:36:40.580
AMONG THE PEOPLE IN THE FIELD
WHO WERE COLLECTING FAMILIES

01:36:40.580 --> 01:36:44.050
AND STUDYING THE PATTERNS
OF INHERITANCE

01:36:44.050 --> 01:36:46.219
BECAUSE NOW THEY WERE ABLE

01:36:46.219 --> 01:36:49.255
TO TAKE ALL THE INFORMATION
THAT THEY HAD

01:36:49.255 --> 01:36:53.159
PUT IT TOGETHER WITH
THE MODERN GENETIC TECHNOLOGY

01:36:53.159 --> 01:36:55.328
AND ACTUALLY FIND A NE.

01:36:57.497 --> 01:37:00.099
Osgood:
THE POWER OF THIS NEW
DNA TECHNOLOGY

01:37:00.099 --> 01:37:03.136
IS FELT IN UTAH, IN PENNSYLVANIA

01:37:03.569 --> 01:37:04.437
EVEN AS FAR AWAY

01:37:04.437 --> 01:37:08.775
AS THE MOUNTAINS
OF COLOMBIA IN SOUTH AMERICA

01:37:09.208 --> 01:37:10.510
WHERE IN 1984

01:37:10.510 --> 01:37:13.546
A CHANCE ENCOUNTER BETWEEN
NEUROLOGIST FRANCISCO LOPERA

01:37:13.980 --> 01:37:15.715
AND A CONFUSED
YOUNG COLOMBIAN PATIENT

01:37:15.715 --> 01:37:19.619
LEADS TO A SEARCH FOR A GENE
FOR ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE.

01:37:19.619 --> 01:37:22.221
Man:
SI, EN MIL NOVECIENTOS
OCHENTA Y CUATRO...

01:37:22.221 --> 01:37:26.559
Translator:
IN 1984, A PATIENT
FROM VELMIRA CAME HERE

01:37:26.559 --> 01:37:32.198
WITH SYMPTOMS OF PROGRESSIVE
MENTAL DISORDER AND DEMENTIA.

01:37:32.198 --> 01:37:35.668
IT CAUGHT OUR ATTENTION
THAT HE WAS SO YOUNG

01:37:35.668 --> 01:37:38.705
IT CAUGHT OUR ATTENTION
AND WERE ABLE TO PIECE TOGETHERE
WENT TO VELMIRA

01:37:38.705 --> 01:37:43.042
NINE OTHER CASES
OF SICK PEOPLE IN THAT FAMILY.

01:37:48.247 --> 01:37:52.151
Osgood:
IN TOWN AFTER TOWN,
DR. LOPERA HEARS STORIES

01:37:52.151 --> 01:37:56.055
OF OTHERS WITH ALZHEIMER'S,
INCLUDING LEONARDO PIEDRAHITA

01:37:56.055 --> 01:38:00.300
WHHE MARKET
WITH HIS DAUGHTER AND GRANDSON.

01:38:02.128 --> 01:38:05.598
LEONARDO WAS DIAGNOSED
WITH ALZHEIMER'S AT AGE 42--

01:38:05.598 --> 01:38:07.767
IN THE PRIME OF LIFE.

01:38:07.767 --> 01:38:09.936
GETTING ALZHEIMER'S
THIS YOUNG IS RARE.

01:38:10.369 --> 01:38:14.273
95% OF THE TIME,
THE DISEASE STRIKES MUCH LATER

01:38:14.707 --> 01:38:18.177
SOMETIMES AS MUCH
AS 20 TO 30 YEARS LATER.

01:38:19.479 --> 01:38:22.515
THIS DISEASE EMERGES
SOMETIMES AS MUCH
AS 2SO EARLY IN LIFETER.WHY

01:38:22.515 --> 01:38:24.684
IS A MYSTERY TO THE TOWNSPEOPLE.

01:38:27.720 --> 01:38:30.323
SOME VERY INTERESTING IDEAS
ABOUT THIS D

01:38:30.323 --> 01:38:33.359
WHY ONE PERSON WOULD GET THE
DISEASE AND ANOTHER WOULD NOT.

01:38:33.359 --> 01:38:37.263
AND ONE OF THE IDEAS WHICH
ACTUALLY WAS QUITE INTERESTING

01:38:37.263 --> 01:38:40.299
WAS THAT SOME FAMILIES BELIEVED

01:38:40.299 --> 01:38:42.902
THAT IF THEY TOUCHED
A CERTAIN TREE IN A VILLAGE

01:38:42.902 --> 01:38:44.637
THEY WOULD GET THE DISEASE

01:38:44.637 --> 01:38:47.240
BUT THEY DIDN'T KNOW WHICH TREE.

01:38:47.240 --> 01:38:48.975
NO ERA UNA CREENCIA
DE TODAS LAS PERSONAS

01:38:48.975 --> 01:38:51.577
PERO SI HABIA ALGUNAS PERSONAS
QUE TENIAN ESA IDEA.

01:38:51.577 --> 01:38:55.047
Translator:
NOT EVERYONE BELIEVED THAT,
BUT SOME DID.

01:38:55.047 --> 01:38:58.518
BUT OTHERS THOUGHT IT WAS
A PUNISHMENT FROM GOD

01:38:58.518 --> 01:39:00.686
AND A FEW THOUGHT
IT WAS HEREDITARY

01:39:00.686 --> 01:39:02.421
BECAUSE THEY HAD OBSERVED

01:39:02.421 --> 01:39:08.928
THAT A GOOD NUMBER
OF FAMILY MEMBERS GOT SICK.

01:39:08.928 --> 01:39:11.097
THEY CALLED IT
"THE IDIOCY OF OUR FAMILY."

01:39:11.531 --> 01:39:12.398
...DE NUESTRA FAMILIA.

01:39:15.001 --> 01:39:17.170
EL TRES CON EL CUATRO.

01:39:17.170 --> 01:39:18.471
SIGUE.

01:39:22.809 --> 01:39:24.977
Osgood:
ALZHEIMER'S IS DEVASTATING

01:39:24.977 --> 01:39:26.712
REGARDLESS
OF WHO GETS IT OR WHY.

01:39:26.712 --> 01:39:29.315
LEONARDO'S DISEASE
IS SO ADVANCED

01:39:29.315 --> 01:39:33.219
HE CANNOT EVEN PERFORM
THE SIMPLEST OF MENTAL TASKS.

01:39:35.822 --> 01:39:37.557
PERO ES QUE NO VEO... OJALA.

01:39:37.557 --> 01:39:38.858
NO, NO, NO.

01:39:38.858 --> 01:39:40.593
Lopera:
PEGUE EL DOS
