01:45:01.580 --> 01:45:04.617
FROM THE GENETIC LEVEL
THROUGH THE BRAIN LEVEL

01:45:04.617 --> 01:45:07.219
TO THE BEHAVIOL,
TO THE EXPERIENTIAL LEVEL

01:45:07.219 --> 01:45:09.388
AND BACK DOWN
THE OTHER DIRECTION--

01:45:09.388 --> 01:45:13.292
AND TO DO IT AROUND A...
AN AREA OF HUMAN EXPERIENCE

01:45:13.292 --> 01:45:15.461
TICAL
TO OUR UNDERSTANDING

01:45:15.461 --> 01:45:18.931
OF WHAT WE'RE ALL ABOUT:
OUR CAPACITY TO REMEMBER

01:45:18.931 --> 01:45:21.967
TO REMEMBER
THE STORY OF OUR LIVES.

01:45:23.702 --> 01:45:25.871
Osgood:
GENETICISTS WON A GREAT VICTORY

01:45:25.871 --> 01:45:31.076
WHEN THEY DISCOVERED ONE GENE
FOR RARE FAMILIAL ALZHEIMER'S

01:45:31.076 --> 01:45:34.547
BUT WHEN IT COMES TO THE MORE
COMMON OLD-AGE VARIETY

01:45:34.547 --> 01:45:36.282
IT'S A DIFFERENT STORY.

01:45:36.282 --> 01:45:39.318
SCIENTISTS ARE IDENTIFYING
MULTIPLE GENES--

01:45:39.318 --> 01:45:42.788
GENES THAT DON'T NECESSARILY
LEAD TO THE DISEASE

01:45:42.788 --> 01:45:45.824
BUT PUT PEOPLE AT RISK
FOR DEVELOPING IT.

01:45:45.824 --> 01:45:50.596
THE SAME HOLDS TRUE FOR OTHER
MENTAL OR BEHAVIORAL DISORDERS

01:45:50.596 --> 01:45:52.765
SUCH AS SCHIZOPHRENIA--

01:45:52.765 --> 01:45:56.235
AS COMMON TODAY
AS IT WAS IN THE 1950s.

01:45:57.970 --> 01:46:01.874
HERE, TOO, MULTIPLE RISK GENES
MAY BE RESPONSIBLE.

01:46:04.910 --> 01:46:07.513
AND LIFE EXPERIENCE MAY
ALSO PLAY A ROLE.

01:46:07.513 --> 01:46:10.983
FOR EXAMPLE, BEING
SEVERELY MALNOURISHED

01:46:10.983 --> 01:46:13.152
DURING PRENATAL DEVELOPMENT

01:46:13.152 --> 01:46:15.754
MAY TRIGGER
SCHIZOPHRENIA YEARS LATER.

01:46:15.754 --> 01:46:22.695
IDEAS ABOUT THE CAUSES OF HUMAN
BEHAVIOR CONTINUE TO BE REFINED

01:46:22.695 --> 01:46:25.297
AS IN THE CASE
OF SHELL SHOCK, FOR EXAMPLE...

01:46:26.599 --> 01:46:30.936
TODAY CALLED
POST-TRAUMATIC STRESS DISORDER.

01:46:31.370 --> 01:46:33.105
WHY DO SOME SOLDIERS BREAK DOWN

01:46:33.105 --> 01:46:36.575
WHILE OTHERS CAN WITHSTAND
THE HORRORS AROUND THEM?

01:46:36.575 --> 01:46:40.045
SCIENTISTS NOW SPECULATE
THAT SOME ARE MORE SUSCEPTIBLE

01:46:40.045 --> 01:46:42.214
PERHAPS GENETICALLY PREDISPOSED

01:46:42.214 --> 01:46:44.817
TO SUCCUMB
TO THE TRAUMAS OF WAR.

01:46:44.817 --> 01:46:49.154
AND YET THESE SOLDIERS STILL
NEED THE TRIGGER OF COMBAT

01:46:49.154 --> 01:46:51.323
TO CAUSE THEIR BREAKDOWN--

01:46:51.323 --> 01:46:53.926
BIOLOGYANDEXPERIENCE.

01:46:56.962 --> 01:47:00.866
MOST SITUATIONS, HOWEVER,
ARE NOT AS RADICAL AS WAR

01:47:00.866 --> 01:47:03.902
AND MOST BEHAVIORS ARE
NOT AS EXTREME

01:47:03.902 --> 01:47:06.071
AS SHELL SHOCK
OR SCHIZOPHRENIA.

01:47:06.071 --> 01:47:10.409
IT IS IN THE MORE ROUTINE
ENCOUNTERS OF EVERYDAY LIFE

01:47:10.409 --> 01:47:13.012
THAT SCIENTISTS
OF HUMAN BEHAVIOR WILL FIND

01:47:13.012 --> 01:47:15.180
THEIR GREATEST CHALLENGE.

01:47:16.482 --> 01:47:21.253
THE MORE WE LEARN ABOUT
OUR BIOLOGY AND THE ENVIRONMENT

01:47:21.253 --> 01:47:23.422
THE MORE WE REALIZE

01:47:23.422 --> 01:47:26.892
HOW DIFFICULT IT IS
TO UNDERSTAND THEIR INTERPLAY.

01:47:29.495 --> 01:47:32.965
Kosik:
SCIENTISTS HAVE MADE ENORMOUS
PROGRESS IN THE PAST CENTURY.

01:47:32.965 --> 01:47:35.567
WE KNOW NEARLY ALL OF OUR GENES.

01:47:35.567 --> 01:47:38.604
WE KNOW A LOT
ABOUT THE MOLECULES IN THE BRAIN

01:47:38.604 --> 01:47:42.074
AND HOW THEY WORK
AND HOW THEY BUILD A BRAIN.

01:47:42.074 --> 01:47:45.978
WE KNOW A BIT ABOUT
HOW THE ENVIRONMENT INTERFACES

01:47:45.978 --> 01:47:48.147
WITH THESE GENES
AND THE MOLECULES

01:47:48.147 --> 01:47:51.617
TO ACTUALLY AFFECT
THEIR EXPRESSION.

01:47:51.617 --> 01:47:54.653
WHAT THE CHALLENGE IS
FOR SCIENTISTS NOW

01:47:54.653 --> 01:47:58.557
IS TO UNDERSTAND HOW ALL
OF THESE MOLECULES AND GENES

01:47:58.557 --> 01:48:00.726
AND ENVIRONMENT WORK TOGETHER

01:48:00.726 --> 01:48:05.931
TO BUILD SOMETHING
AS COMPLEX AS HUMAN BEHAVIOR

01:48:05.931 --> 01:48:09.401
WHICH IS CLEARLY MORE
THAN THE SUM OF THE PARTS.

01:48:09.401 --> 01:48:12.438
THAT'S REALLY THE CHALLENGE
OF THE 21st CENTURY.

